<p id=3D"index-14">Notes:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic">
<li><p>Also referred to as integer division.  For operands of type <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions=
.html#int" title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int</span></code></a>,
the result has type <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.py=
thon.org/3/library/functions.html#int" title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py=
 py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int</span></cod=
e></a>.  For operands of type <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https=
://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code cl=
ass=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">f=
loat</span></code></a>,
the result has type <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.py=
thon.org/3/library/functions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xre=
f py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span=
></code></a>.  In general, the result is a whole
integer, though the result=E2=80=99s type is not necessarily <a class=3D"re=
ference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#=
int" title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notrans=
late"><span class=3D"pre">int</span></code></a>.  The result is
always rounded towards minus infinity: <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">1//2</span></code> is <code class=3D"docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code>, <code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">(-1)//2</span></code> is
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-1</span><=
/code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">1/=
/(-2)</span></code> is <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">-1</span></code>, and <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">(-1)//(-2)</span></code> is <code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>Not for complex numbers.  Instead convert to floats using <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions=
.html#abs" title=3D"abs"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal no=
translate"><span class=3D"pre">abs()</span></code></a> if
appropriate.</p></li>
<li><p id=3D"index-15">Conversion from <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#float" title=3D"float"=
><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">float</span></code></a> to <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D=
"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int" title=3D"int"><code =
class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre"=
>int</span></code></a> truncates, discarding the
fractional part. See functions <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/math.html#math.floor" title=3D"math.floor"><c=
ode class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">math.floor()</span></code></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/math.html#math.ceil" title=3D"math.ce=
il"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span clas=
s=3D"pre">math.ceil()</span></code></a> for
alternative conversions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>float also accepts the strings =E2=80=9Cnan=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cin=
f=E2=80=9D with an optional prefix =E2=80=9C+=E2=80=9D
or =E2=80=9C-=E2=80=9D for Not a Number (NaN) and positive or negative infi=
nity.</p></li>
<li><p>Python defines <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">pow(0,</span> <span class=3D"pre">0)</span></code> and <code cl=
ass=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"pre">**</span> <span class=3D"pre">0</span></code> to be <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">1</span></code>, as i=
s common for
programming languages.</p></li>
<li><p>The numeric literals accepted include the digits <code class=3D"docu=
tils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code> to <code clas=
s=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">9</span></code> or a=
ny
Unicode equivalent (code points with the <code class=3D"docutils literal no=
translate"><span class=3D"pre">Nd</span></code> property).</p>
<p>See <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://unicode.org/Public/U=
NIDATA/extracted/DerivedNumericType.txt">the Unicode Standard</a>
for a complete list of code points with the <code class=3D"docutils literal=
 notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Nd</span></code> property.</p>
</li>
</ol>
