<section id=3D"bitwise-operations-on-integer-types">
<span id=3D"bitstring-ops"></span><h3>Bitwise Operations on Integer Types<a=
 class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.ht=
ml#bitwise-operations-on-integer-types" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=
=B6</a></h3>
<p id=3D"index-16">Bitwise operations only make sense for integers. The res=
ult of bitwise
operations is calculated as though carried out in two=E2=80=99s complement =
with an
infinite number of sign bits.</p>
<p>The priorities of the binary bitwise operations are all lower than the n=
umeric
operations and higher than the comparisons; the unary operation <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">~</span></code> has t=
he
same priority as the other unary numeric operations (<code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">+</span></code> and <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-</span></code>).</p>
<p>This table lists the bitwise operations sorted in ascending priority:</p=
>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Operation</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Result</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">|</span> <span class=3D"pr=
e">y</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>bitwise <em class=3D"dfn">or</em> of <em>x</em> and
<em>y</em></p></td>
<td><p>(4)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">^</span> <span class=3D"pre=
">y</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>bitwise <em class=3D"dfn">exclusive or</em> of
<em>x</em> and <em>y</em></p></td>
<td><p>(4)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">&amp;</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">y</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>bitwise <em class=3D"dfn">and</em> of <em>x</em> and
<em>y</em></p></td>
<td><p>(4)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">n</span></code></p></td>
<td><p><em>x</em> shifted left by <em>n</em> bits</p></td>
<td><p>(1)(2)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">&gt;&gt;</span> <span clas=
s=3D"pre">n</span></code></p></td>
<td><p><em>x</em> shifted right by <em>n</em> bits</p></td>
<td><p>(1)(3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">~x</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>the bits of <em>x</em> inverted</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple">
<li><p>Negative shift counts are illegal and cause a <a class=3D"reference =
internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#ValueEr=
ror" title=3D"ValueError"><code class=3D"xref py py-exc docutils literal no=
translate"><span class=3D"pre">ValueError</span></code></a> to be raised.</=
p></li>
<li><p>A left shift by <em>n</em> bits is equivalent to multiplication by <=
code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">pow(2,</spa=
n> <span class=3D"pre">n)</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>A right shift by <em>n</em> bits is equivalent to floor division by =
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">pow(2,</sp=
an> <span class=3D"pre">n)</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>Performing these calculations with at least one extra sign extension=
 bit in
a finite two=E2=80=99s complement representation (a working bit-width of
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">1</span> <=
span class=3D"pre">+</span> <span class=3D"pre">max(x.bit_length(),</span> =
<span class=3D"pre">y.bit_length())</span></code> or more) is sufficient to=
 get the
same result as if there were an infinite number of sign bits.</p></li>
</ol>
</section>
<section id=3D"additional-methods-on-integer-types">
<h3>Additional Methods on Integer Types<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#additional-methods-on-integer-t=
ypes" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p>The int type implements the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/numbers.html#numbers.Integral" title=3D"numbe=
rs.Integral"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">numbers.Integral</span></code></a> <a class=3D"referenc=
e internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-abstract-b=
ase-class"><span class=3D"xref std std-term">abstract base
class</span></a>. In addition, it provides a few more methods:</p>
<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"int.bit_length">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">int.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">bit_length</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span=
><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes=
.html#int.bit_length" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return the number of bits necessary to represent an integer in binar=
y,
excluding the sign and leading zeros:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">n</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <=
span class=3D"o">-</span><span class=3D"mi">37</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">bin</span><span c=
lass=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'-0b100101'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span clas=
s=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">bit_length</span><span class=3D"p">()</sp=
an>
<span class=3D"go">6</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>More precisely, if <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">x</span></code> is nonzero, then <code class=3D"docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">x.bit_length()</span></code> is the
unique positive integer <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">k</span></code> such that <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">2**(k-1)</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;=3D</=
span> <span class=3D"pre">abs(x)</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;</span> <sp=
an class=3D"pre">2**k</span></code>.
Equivalently, when <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">abs(x)</span></code> is small enough to have a correctly
rounded logarithm, then <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">k</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">1=
</span> <span class=3D"pre">+</span> <span class=3D"pre">int(log(abs(x),</s=
pan> <span class=3D"pre">2))</span></code>.
If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">x</span=
></code> is zero, then <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">x.bit_length()</span></code> returns <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code>.</p>
<p>Equivalent to:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"k">def=
</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">bit_length</span><span =
class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"bp">self</span><span class=3D"p">):</spa=
n>
    <span class=3D"n">s</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"=
nb">bin</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"bp">self</span><span=
 class=3D"p">)</span>       <span class=3D"c1"># binary representation:  bi=
n(-37) --&gt; '-0b100101'</span>
    <span class=3D"n">s</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"=
n">s</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">lstrip</span><span c=
lass=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'-0b'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span=
> <span class=3D"c1"># remove leading zeros and minus sign</span>
    <span class=3D"k">return</span> <span class=3D"nb">len</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">s</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>       =
<span class=3D"c1"># len('100101') --&gt; 6</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.1.</span></p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

