<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"int.to_bytes">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">int.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">to_bytes</span><=
/span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=
=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">length</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span clas=
s=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre=
">1</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">byteorder</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span class=3D"pre">=3D=
</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre">'big'</span=
></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"keyword-only-separato=
r o"><abbr title=3D"Keyword-only parameters separator (PEP 3102)"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">*</span></abbr></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=
=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">signed</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span clas=
s=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre=
">False</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"hea=
derlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#int.to_byt=
es" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return an array of bytes representing an integer.</p>
<div class=3D"doctest highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highligh=
t" style=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"butto=
n" title=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=
=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">10=
24</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D=
"n">to_bytes</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">2</span><sp=
an class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">byteorder</span><span class=3D"o"=
>=3D</span><span class=3D"s1">'big'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'\x04\x00'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span clas=
s=3D"mi">1024</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">to_bytes</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">=
10</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">byteorder</span><span=
 class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"s1">'big'</span><span class=3D"p">)</=
span>
<span class=3D"go">b'\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x04\x00'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span clas=
s=3D"o">-</span><span class=3D"mi">1024</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><sp=
an class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">to_bytes</span><span class=3D"p">(=
</span><span class=3D"mi">10</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=
=3D"n">byteorder</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"s1">'big'=
</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">signed</span><span clas=
s=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'\xff\xff\xff\xff\xff\xff\xff\xff\xfc\x00'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">x</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"mi">1000</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">x</span><span clas=
s=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">to_bytes</span><span class=3D"p">((</span=
><span class=3D"n">x</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">bit_=
length</span><span class=3D"p">()</span> <span class=3D"o">+</span> <span c=
lass=3D"mi">7</span><span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">//</span> =
<span class=3D"mi">8</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">byt=
eorder</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"s1">'little'</span>=
<span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'\xe8\x03'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The integer is represented using <em>length</em> bytes, and defaults to =
1.  An
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/e=
xceptions.html#OverflowError" title=3D"OverflowError"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">OverflowError</s=
pan></code></a> is raised if the integer is not representable with
the given number of bytes.</p>
<p>The <em>byteorder</em> argument determines the byte order used to repres=
ent the
integer, and defaults to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">"big"</span></code>.  If <em>byteorder</em> is
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">"big"</spa=
n></code>, the most significant byte is at the beginning of the byte
array.  If <em>byteorder</em> is <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">"little"</span></code>, the most significant byte is=
 at
the end of the byte array.</p>
<p>The <em>signed</em> argument determines whether two=E2=80=99s complement=
 is used to
represent the integer.  If <em>signed</em> is <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">False</span></code> and a negative inte=
ger is
given, an <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/exceptions.html#OverflowError" title=3D"OverflowError"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Overfl=
owError</span></code></a> is raised. The default value for <em>signed</em>
is <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">False</=
span></code>.</p>
<p>The default values can be used to conveniently turn an integer into a
single byte object:</p>
