cs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#additional-methods-on-complex" title=
=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p>The <code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">complex</span></code> type implements the <a class=3D"referen=
ce internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/numbers.html#numbers=
.Complex" title=3D"numbers.Complex"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">numbers.Complex</span></code></a=
>
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.=
html#term-abstract-base-class"><span class=3D"xref std std-term">abstract b=
ase class</span></a>.
<code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">complex</span></code> also has the following additional methods.</=
p>
<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"complex.from_number">
<em class=3D"property"><span class=3D"k"><span class=3D"pre">classmethod</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"w"> </span></em><span class=3D"sig-prename desccl=
assname"><span class=3D"pre">complex.</span></span><span class=3D"sig-name =
descname"><span class=3D"pre">from_number</span></span><span class=3D"sig-p=
aren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre"=
>x</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerli=
nk" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#complex.from_nu=
mber" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Class method to convert a number to a complex number.</p>
<p>For a general Python object <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">x</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notra=
nslate"><span class=3D"pre">complex.from_number(x)</span></code> delegates =
to
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">x.__comple=
x__()</span></code>.  If <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://do=
cs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__complex__" title=3D"objec=
t.__complex__"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">__complex__()</span></code></a> is not defined then it=
 falls back
to <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/refere=
nce/datamodel.html#object.__float__" title=3D"object.__float__"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">__flo=
at__()</span></code></a>.  If <code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">__float__()</span></code> is not define=
d then it falls back
to <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/refere=
nce/datamodel.html#object.__index__" title=3D"object.__index__"><code class=
