<section id=3D"hashing-of-numeric-types">
<span id=3D"numeric-hash"></span><h3>Hashing of numeric types<a class=3D"he=
aderlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#hashing-o=
f-numeric-types" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p>For numbers <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"=
pre">x</span></code> and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">y</span></code>, possibly of different types, it=E2=80=99s a=
 requirement
that <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">hash(=
x)</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">hash(y)</sp=
an></code> whenever <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span clas=
s=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">y<=
/span></code> (see the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs=
.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__hash__" title=3D"object.__h=
ash__"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">__hash__()</span></code></a>
method documentation for more details).  For ease of implementation and
efficiency across a variety of numeric types (including <a class=3D"referen=
ce internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int" =
title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">int</span></code></a>,
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docuti=
ls literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span></code></a>, <a cla=
ss=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal=
.html#decimal.Decimal" title=3D"decimal.Decimal"><code class=3D"xref py py-=
class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">decimal.Decimal</sp=
an></code></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyt=
hon.org/3/library/fractions.html#fractions.Fraction" title=3D"fractions.Fra=
ction"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">fractions.Fraction</span></code></a>)
Python=E2=80=99s hash for numeric types is based on a single mathematical f=
unction
that=E2=80=99s defined for any rational number, and hence applies to all in=
stances of
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#int" title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int</span></code></a> and <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/fractions=
.html#fractions.Fraction" title=3D"fractions.Fraction"><code class=3D"xref =
py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">fractions.Fra=
ction</span></code></a>, and all finite instances of
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docuti=
ls literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span></code></a> and <a =
class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/deci=
mal.html#decimal.Decimal" title=3D"decimal.Decimal"><code class=3D"xref py =
py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">decimal.Decimal<=
/span></code></a>.  Essentially, this function is
given by reduction modulo <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><spa=
n class=3D"pre">P</span></code> for a fixed prime <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">P</span></code>.  The value of <cod=
e class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">P</span></code=
> is
made available to Python as the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"htt=
ps://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.html#sys.hash_info.modulus" title=3D"sys=
.hash_info.modulus"><code class=3D"xref py py-attr docutils literal notrans=
late"><span class=3D"pre">modulus</span></code></a> attribute of
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
ys.html#sys.hash_info" title=3D"sys.hash_info"><code class=3D"xref py py-da=
ta docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.hash_info</span></=
code></a>.</p>
<div class=3D"impl-detail compound">
<p><strong>CPython implementation detail:</strong> Currently, the prime use=
d is <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">P</sp=
an> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">2**31</span> <span c=
lass=3D"pre">-</span> <span class=3D"pre">1</span></code> on machines with =
32-bit C
longs and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
P</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">2**61</span> <s=
pan class=3D"pre">-</span> <span class=3D"pre">1</span></code> on machines =
with 64-bit C longs.</p>
</div>
<p>Here are the rules in detail:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
x</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">m</span> <span =
class=3D"pre">/</span> <span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> is a nonnegative=
 rational number and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">n</span></code> is not divisible
by <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">P</span=
></code>, define <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">hash(x)</span></code> as <code class=3D"docutils literal notransla=
te"><span class=3D"pre">m</span> <span class=3D"pre">*</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">invmod(n,</span> <span class=3D"pre">P)</span> <span class=3D"pre"=
>%</span> <span class=3D"pre">P</span></code>, where <code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">invmod(n,</span>
<span class=3D"pre">P)</span></code> gives the inverse of <code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> modulo <cod=
e class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">P</span></code=
>.</p></li>
<li><p>If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
x</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">m</span> <span =
class=3D"pre">/</span> <span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> is a nonnegative=
 rational number and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">n</span></code> is
divisible by <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">P</span></code> (but <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">m</span></code> is not) then <code class=3D"docutils literal =
notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> has no inverse
modulo <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">P</=
span></code> and the rule above doesn=E2=80=99t apply; in this case define
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">hash(x)</s=
pan></code> to be the constant value <code class=3D"docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.hash_info.inf</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
x</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">m</span> <span =
class=3D"pre">/</span> <span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> is a negative ra=
tional number define <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">hash(x)</span></code>
as <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-hash(-=
x)</span></code>.  If the resulting hash is <code class=3D"docutils literal=
 notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-1</span></code>, replace it with
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-2</span><=
/code>.</p></li>
<li><p>The particular values <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">sys.hash_info.inf</span></code> and <code class=3D"docut=
ils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-sys.hash_info.inf</span></cod=
e>
are used as hash values for positive
infinity or negative infinity (respectively).</p></li>
<li><p>For a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/functions.html#complex" title=3D"complex"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">complex</span>=
</code></a> number <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">z</span></code>, the hash values of the real
and imaginary parts are combined by computing <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">hash(z.real)</span> <span class=3D"pre"=
>+</span>
<span class=3D"pre">sys.hash_info.imag</span> <span class=3D"pre">*</span> =
<span class=3D"pre">hash(z.imag)</span></code>, reduced modulo
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">2**sys.has=
h_info.width</span></code> so that it lies in
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">range(-2**=
(sys.hash_info.width</span> <span class=3D"pre">-</span> <span class=3D"pre=
">1),</span> <span class=3D"pre">2**(sys.hash_info.width</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">-</span>
<span class=3D"pre">1))</span></code>.  Again, if the result is <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-1</span></code>, it=
=E2=80=99s replaced with <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">-2</span></code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>To clarify the above rules, here=E2=80=99s some example Python code,
equivalent to the built-in hash, for computing the hash of a rational
number, <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/l=
ibrary/functions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xref py py-clas=
s docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span></code></a>=
, or <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libr=
ary/functions.html#complex" title=3D"complex"><code class=3D"xref py py-cla=
ss docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">complex</span></code><=
/a>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
