n> <span class=3D"s2">"eggs"</span>
<span class=3D"go">True</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
<li><p>Values of <em>n</em> less than <code class=3D"docutils literal notra=
nslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code> are treated as <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code> (which yie=
lds an empty
sequence of the same type as <em>s</em>).  Note that items in the sequence =
<em>s</em>
are not copied; they are referenced multiple times.  This often haunts
