tuted.  But note that <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">-0</span></code> is
still <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</s=
pan></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>The slice of <em>s</em> from <em>i</em> to <em>j</em> is defined as =
the sequence of items with
index <em>k</em> such that <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><sp=
an class=3D"pre">i</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;=3D</span> <span class=3D=
"pre">k</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;</span> <span class=3D"pre">j</span>=
</code>.</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>If <em>i</em> is omitted or <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code>, use <code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>If <em>j</em> is omitted or <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code>, use <code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">len(s)</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>If <em>i</em> or <em>j</em> is less than <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-len(s)</span></code>, use <code clas=
s=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span></code>.</p>=
</li>
<li><p>If <em>i</em> or <em>j</em> is greater than <code class=3D"docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">len(s)</span></code>, use <code cl=
ass=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">len(s)</span></cod=
e>.</p></li>
<li><p>If <em>i</em> is greater than or equal to <em>j</em>, the slice is e=
mpty.</p></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>The slice of <em>s</em> from <em>i</em> to <em>j</em> with step <em>=
k</em> is defined as the sequence of
items with index  <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
