i>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Some sequence types (such as <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D=
"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#range" title=3D"range"><co=
de class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">range</span></code></a>) only support item sequences
that follow specific patterns, and hence don=E2=80=99t support sequence
concatenation or repetition.</p></li>
<li><p>An <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/exceptions.html#IndexError" title=3D"IndexError"><code class=3D"xr=
ef py py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">IndexError</=
span></code></a> is raised if <em>i</em> is outside the sequence range.</p>=
</li>
</ol>
<p class=3D"rubric">Sequence Methods</p>
<p>Sequence types also support the following methods:</p>
<dl class=3D"py method" id=3D"list.count">
<span id=3D"range.count"></span><span id=3D"tuple.count"></span><dt class=
=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"sequence.count">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">sequence.</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">count</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span cla=
ss=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">value</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-par=
am"><span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-o=
nly parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></spa=
n></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"ht=
tps://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#sequence.count" title=3D"Link=
 to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return the total number of occurrences of <em>value</em> in <em>sequ=
ence</em>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method" id=3D"list.index">
<span id=3D"range.index"></span><span id=3D"tuple.index"></span><dt class=
=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"sequence.index">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">sequence.</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">index</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">value[,</span> <span class=3D"pre">start[,</span> <span class=3D=
"pre">stop]</span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"header=
link" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#sequence.inde=
x" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return the index of the first occurrence of <em>value</em> in <em>se=
quence</em>.</p>
<p>Raises <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/exceptions.html#ValueError" title=3D"ValueError"><code class=3D"xr=
ef py py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">ValueError</=
span></code></a> if <em>value</em> is not found in <em>sequence</em>.</p>
<p>The <em>start</em> or <em>stop</em> arguments allow for efficient search=
ing
of subsections of the sequence, beginning at <em>start</em> and ending at <=
em>stop</em>.
This is roughly equivalent to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">start</span> <span class=3D"pre">+</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">sequence[start:stop].index(value)</span></code>,
only without copying any data.</p>
<div class=3D"admonition caution">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Caution</p>
<p>Not all sequence types support passing the <em>start</em> and <em>stop</=
em> arguments.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

</section>
<section id=3D"immutable-sequence-types">
<span id=3D"typesseq-immutable"></span><h3>Immutable Sequence Types<a class=
=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#imm=
utable-sequence-types" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p id=3D"index-22">The only operation that immutable sequence types general=
ly implement that is
not also implemented by mutable sequence types is support for the <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions=
.html#hash" title=3D"hash"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal =
notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">hash()</span></code></a>
built-in.</p>
<p>This support allows immutable sequences, such as <a class=3D"reference i=
nternal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#tuple" tit=
le=3D"tuple"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">tuple</span></code></a> instances, to
be used as <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/library/stdtypes.html#dict" title=3D"dict"><code class=3D"xref py py-clas=
s docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">dict</span></code></a> =
keys and stored in <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyt=
hon.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#set" title=3D"set"><code class=3D"xref py p=
y-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">set</span></code>=
</a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/stdtypes.html#frozenset" title=3D"frozenset"><code class=3D"xref py=
 py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">frozenset</span=
></code></a>
instances.</p>
<p>Attempting to hash an immutable sequence that contains unhashable values=
 will
result in <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/exceptions.html#TypeError" title=3D"TypeError"><code class=3D"xref=
 py py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">TypeError</spa=
n></code></a>.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"mutable-sequence-types">
<span id=3D"typesseq-mutable"></span><h3>Mutable Sequence Types<a class=3D"=
headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#mutable=
-sequence-types" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p id=3D"index-23">The operations in the following table are defined on mut=
able sequence types.
The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/collections.abc.html#collections.abc.MutableSequence" title=3D"collectio=
ns.abc.MutableSequence"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal no=
translate"><span class=3D"pre">collections.abc.MutableSequence</span></code=
></a> ABC is provided to make it
easier to correctly implement these operations on custom sequence types.</p=
>
<p>In the table <em>s</em> is an instance of a mutable sequence type, <em>t=
</em> is any
iterable object and <em>x</em> is an arbitrary object that meets any type
and value restrictions imposed by <em>s</em> (for example, <a class=3D"refe=
rence internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#byt=
earray" title=3D"bytearray"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray</span></code></a> only
accepts integers that meet the value restriction <code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;=3D=
</span> <span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">&lt;=3D</span> <sp=
an class=3D"pre">255</span></code>).</p>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault" id=3D"index-24">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Operation</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Result</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">s[i]</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">x</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>item <em>i</em> of <em>s</em> is replaced by
<em>x</em></p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">del</span> <span class=3D"pre">s[i]</span></code></p></t=
d>
<td><p>removes item <em>i</em> of <em>s</em></p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">s[i:j]</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span clas=
s=3D"pre">t</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>slice of <em>s</em> from <em>i</em> to <em>j</em>
is replaced by the contents of
the iterable <em>t</em></p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">del</span> <span class=3D"pre">s[i:j]</span></code></p><=
/td>
<td><p>removes the elements of
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">s[i:j]</sp=
an></code> from the list
(same as <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">s=
[i:j]</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">[]</span></=
code>)</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">s[i:j:k]</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span cl=
ass=3D"pre">t</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>the elements of <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">s[i:j:k]</span></code>
are replaced by those of <em>t</em></p></td>
<td><p>(1)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">del</span> <span class=3D"pre">s[i:j:k]</span></code></p=
></td>
<td><p>removes the elements of
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">s[i:j:k]</=
span></code> from the list</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">s</span> <span class=3D"pre">+=3D</span> <span class=3D=
"pre">t</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>extends <em>s</em> with the
contents of <em>t</em> (for the
most part the same as
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">s[len(s):l=
en(s)]</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">t</span></=
code>)</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">s</span> <span class=3D"pre">*=3D</span> <span class=3D"=
pre">n</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>updates <em>s</em> with its contents
repeated <em>n</em> times</p></td>
<td><p>(2)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple">
<li><p>If <em>k</em> is not equal to <code class=3D"docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">1</span></code>, <em>t</em> must have the same l=
ength as the slice it is replacing.</p></li>
<li><p>The value <em>n</em> is an integer, or an object implementing
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/reference=
/datamodel.html#object.__index__" title=3D"object.__index__"><code class=3D=
"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">__index_=
_()</span></code></a>.  Zero and negative values of <em>n</em> clear
the sequence.  Items in the sequence are not copied; they are referenced
multiple times, as explained for <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">s</span> <span class=3D"pre">*</span> <span class=3D=
"pre">n</span></code> under <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https:/=
/docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#typesseq-common"><span class=3D"st=
d std-ref">Common Sequence Operations</span></a>.</p></li>
</ol>
<p class=3D"rubric">Mutable Sequence Methods</p>
<p>Mutable sequence types also support the following methods:</p>
<dl class=3D"py method" id=3D"bytearray.append">
<span id=3D"list.append"></span><dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"seque=
nce.append">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">sequence.</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">append</spa=
n></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span cl=
ass=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">value</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-pa=
ram"><span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-=
only parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></sp=
an></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"h=
ttps://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#sequence.append" title=3D"Li=
nk to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Append <em>value</em> to the end of the sequence
This is equivalent to writing <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">seq[len(seq):len(seq)]</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D</=
span> <span class=3D"pre">[value]</span></code>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method" id=3D"bytearray.clear">
<span id=3D"list.clear"></span><dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"sequen=
ce.clear">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">sequence.</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">clear</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span=
><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes=
.html#sequence.clear" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.3.</span></p>
</div>
<p>Remove all items from <em>sequence</em>.
This is equivalent to writing <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">del</span> <span class=3D"pre">sequence[:]</span></code=
>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method" id=3D"bytearray.copy">
<span id=3D"list.copy"></span><dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"sequenc=
e.copy">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">sequence.</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">copy</span>=
</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span>=
<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.=
html#sequence.copy" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.3.</span></p>
</div>
<p>Create a shallow copy of <em>sequence</em>.
This is equivalent to writing <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
