>*</span></abbr></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><sp=
an class=3D"pre">errors</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span=
></dt>
<dd><p>Return a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python=
.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#textseq"><span class=3D"std std-ref">string</s=
pan></a> version of <em>object</em>.  If <em>object</em> is not
provided, returns the empty string.  Otherwise, the behavior of <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str()</span></code>
depends on whether <em>encoding</em> or <em>errors</em> is given, as follow=
s.</p>
<p>If neither <em>encoding</em> nor <em>errors</em> is given, <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str(object)</span></c=
ode> returns
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/reference=
/datamodel.html#object.__str__" title=3D"object.__str__"><code class=3D"xre=
f py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">type(object)=
.__str__(object)</span></code></a>,
which is the =E2=80=9Cinformal=E2=80=9D or nicely
printable string representation of <em>object</em>.  For string objects, th=
is is
the string itself.  If <em>object</em> does not have a <a class=3D"referenc=
e internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#obje=
ct.__str__" title=3D"object.__str__"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">__str__()</span></code></a>
method, then <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-func=
 docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str()</span></code></a> =
falls back to returning
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#repr" title=3D"repr"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">repr(object)</span></code></a>.</p=
>
<p id=3D"index-31">If at least one of <em>encoding</em> or <em>errors</em> =
is given, <em>object</em> should be a
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.=
html#term-bytes-like-object"><span class=3D"xref std std-term">bytes-like o=
bject</span></a> (e.g. <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs=
.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><code class=3D"x=
ref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes</sp=
an></code></a> or <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyth=
on.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytearray" title=3D"bytearray"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">byte=
array</span></code></a>).  In
this case, if <em>object</em> is a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"=
https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><cod=
e class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">bytes</span></code></a> (or <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytearray" title=3D"bytearray">=
<code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">bytearray</span></code></a>) object,
then <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str(b=
ytes,</span> <span class=3D"pre">encoding,</span> <span class=3D"pre">error=
s)</span></code> is equivalent to
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tdtypes.html#bytes.decode" title=3D"bytes.decode"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes.decode(encodi=
ng,</span> <span class=3D"pre">errors)</span></code></a>.  Otherwise, the b=
ytes
object underlying the buffer object is obtained before calling
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tdtypes.html#bytes.decode" title=3D"bytes.decode"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes.decode()</spa=
n></code></a>.  See <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.py=
thon.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#binaryseq"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Bin=
ary Sequence Types =E2=80=94 bytes, bytearray, memoryview</span></a> and
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/buf=
fer.html#bufferobjects"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Buffer Protocol</span><=
/a> for information on buffer objects.</p>
<p>Passing a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><code class=3D"xref py py-=
class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes</span></code>=
</a> object to <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.=
org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-fu=
nc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str()</span></code></a=
> without the <em>encoding</em>
or <em>errors</em> arguments falls under the first case of returning the in=
formal
string representation (see also the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D=
"https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#cmdoption-b"><code class=3D"x=
ref std std-option docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-b</sp=
an></code></a> command-line option to
Python).  For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">str</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><s=
pan class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'Zoot!'</span><span class=3D"p"=
>)</span>
<span class=3D"go">"b'Zoot!'"</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>For more information on the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">str</span></code> class and its methods, see
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tdtypes.html#textseq"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Text Sequence Type =E2=80=
=94 str</span></a> and the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://=
docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#string-methods"><span class=3D"std =
std-ref">String Methods</span></a> section below.  To output
formatted strings, see the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://=
docs.python.org/3/reference/lexical_analysis.html#f-strings"><span class=3D=
"std std-ref">f-strings</span></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/string.html#formatstrings"><span clas=
s=3D"std std-ref">Format String Syntax</span></a>
sections.  In addition, see the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"htt=
ps://docs.python.org/3/library/text.html#stringservices"><span class=3D"std=
 std-ref">Text Processing Services</span></a> section.</p>
</dd></dl>

<section id=3D"string-methods">
<span id=3D"index-32"></span><span id=3D"id5"></span><h3>String Methods<a c=
lass=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html=
#string-methods" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p id=3D"index-33">Strings implement all of the <a class=3D"reference inter=
nal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#typesseq-commo=
n"><span class=3D"std std-ref">common</span></a> sequence
operations, along with the additional methods described below.</p>
<p>Strings also support two styles of string formatting, one providing a la=
rge
degree of flexibility and customization (see <a class=3D"reference internal=
" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.format" title=
=3D"str.format"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">str.format()</span></code></a>,
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tring.html#formatstrings"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Format String Syntax<=
/span></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.=
org/3/library/string.html#string-formatting"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Cu=
stom String Formatting</span></a>) and the other based on C
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">printf</sp=
an></code> style formatting that handles a narrower range of types and is
slightly harder to use correctly, but is often faster for the cases it can
handle (<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/l=
ibrary/stdtypes.html#old-string-formatting"><span class=3D"std std-ref">pri=
ntf-style String Formatting</span></a>).</p>
<p>The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/text.html#textservices"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Text Processing S=
ervices</span></a> section of the standard library covers a number of
other modules that provide various text related utilities (including regula=
r
expression support in the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://d=
ocs.python.org/3/library/re.html#module-re" title=3D"re: Regular expression=
 operations."><code class=3D"xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">re</span></code></a> module).</p>
<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.capitalize">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">capitalize</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span=
><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes=
.html#str.capitalize" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the string with its first character capitalized and=
 the
rest lowercased.</p>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.8: </span>T=
he first character is now put into titlecase rather than uppercase.
This means that characters like digraphs will only have their first
letter capitalized, instead of the full character.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.casefold">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">casefold</span><=
/span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><=
a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.h=
tml#str.casefold" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a casefolded copy of the string. Casefolded strings may be us=
ed for
caseless matching.</p>
<p>Casefolding is similar to lowercasing but more aggressive because it is
intended to remove all case distinctions in a string. For example, the Germ=
an
lowercase letter <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">'=C3=9F'</span></code> is equivalent to <code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">"ss"</span></code>. Since it is alre=
ady
lowercase, <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/library/stdtypes.html#str.lower" title=3D"str.lower"><code class=3D"xref =
py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">lower()</span>=
</code></a> would do nothing to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">'=C3=9F'</span></code>; <a class=3D"reference interna=
l" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.casefold" ti=
tle=3D"str.casefold"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">casefold()</span></code></a>
converts it to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"=
pre">"ss"</span></code>.
For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-pycon notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'stra=C3=9Fe'</span><span class=3D"o">=
.</span><span class=3D"n">lower</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">'stra=C3=9Fe'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'stra=C3=9Fe'</sp=
an><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">casefold</span><span class=
=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">'strasse'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The casefolding algorithm is
<a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://www.unicode.org/versions/Un=
icode16.0.0/core-spec/chapter-3/#G33992">described in section 3.13 =E2=80=
=98Default Case Folding=E2=80=99 of the Unicode Standard</a>.</p>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.3.</span></p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.center">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">center</span></s=
pan><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=
=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">width</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param=
"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">fillchar</span></span><span class=
=3D"o"><span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><=
span class=3D"pre">'</span> <span class=3D"pre">'</span></span></em>, <em c=
lass=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=
=3D"Positional-only parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</s=
pan></abbr></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"header=
link" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.center" t=
itle=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return centered in a string of length <em>width</em>. Padding is don=
e using the
specified <em>fillchar</em> (default is an ASCII space). The original strin=
g is
returned if <em>width</em> is less than or equal to <code class=3D"docutils=
 literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">len(s)</span></code>.  For exampl=
e:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'Python'</span><span class=3D"o">.</sp=
an><span class=3D"n">center</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"=
mi">10</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'  Python  '</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'Python'</span><s=
pan class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">center</span><span class=3D"p">(<=
/span><span class=3D"mi">10</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D=
"s1">'-'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'--Python--'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'Python'</span><s=
pan class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">center</span><span class=3D"p">(<=
/span><span class=3D"mi">4</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'Python'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.count">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">count</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D=
"n"><span class=3D"pre">sub</span></span></em><span class=3D"optional">[</s=
pan>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">start</=
span></span></em><span class=3D"optional">[</span>, <em class=3D"sig-param"=
><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">end</span></span></em><span class=3D=
"optional">]</span><span class=3D"optional">]</span><span class=3D"sig-pare=
n">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/librar=
y/stdtypes.html#str.count" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt=
>
<dd><p>Return the number of non-overlapping occurrences of substring <em>su=
b</em> in the
range [<em>start</em>, <em>end</em>].  Optional arguments <em>start</em> an=
d <em>end</em> are
interpreted as in slice notation.</p>
<p>If <em>sub</em> is empty, returns the number of empty strings between ch=
aracters
which is the length of the string plus one. For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'spam, spam, spam'</span><span class=
=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">count</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><spa=
n class=3D"s1">'spam'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">3</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'spam, spam, spam=
'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">count</span><span class=
=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'spam'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <=
span class=3D"mi">5</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">2</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'spam, spam, spam=
'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">count</span><span class=
=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'spam'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <=
span class=3D"mi">5</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"mi">10<=
/span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">1</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'spam, spam, spam=
'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">count</span><span class=
=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'eggs'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">0</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'spam, spam, spam=
'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">count</span><span class=
=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">''</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">17</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.encode">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">encode</span></s=
pan><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=
=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">encoding</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"p=
re">'utf-8'</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><=
span class=3D"pre">errors</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span class=3D"pre=
">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre">'stric=
t'</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerli=
nk" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.encode" tit=
le=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return the string encoded to <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D=
"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><co=
de class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">bytes</span></code></a>.</p>
<p><em>encoding</em> defaults to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">'utf-8'</span></code>;
see <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/codecs.html#standard-encodings"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Standard Enc=
odings</span></a> for possible values.</p>
<p><em>errors</em> controls how encoding errors are handled.
If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'strict=
'</span></code> (the default), a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"ht=
tps://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#UnicodeError" title=3D"Unic=
odeError"><code class=3D"xref py py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">UnicodeError</span></code></a> exception is raised.
Other possible values are <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><spa=
n class=3D"pre">'ignore'</span></code>,
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'replace'<=
/span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"=
pre">'xmlcharrefreplace'</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'backslashreplace'</span></code> and any
other name registered via <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://d=
ocs.python.org/3/library/codecs.html#codecs.register_error" title=3D"codecs=
.register_error"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">codecs.register_error()</span></code></a>.
See <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/codecs.html#error-handlers"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Error Handlers</=
span></a> for details.</p>
<p>For performance reasons, the value of <em>errors</em> is not checked for=
 validity
unless an encoding error actually occurs,
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/d=
evmode.html#devmode"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Python Development Mode</s=
pan></a> is enabled
or a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/usin=
g/configure.html#debug-build"><span class=3D"std std-ref">debug build</span=
></a> is used.
For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">encoded_str_to_bytes</span> <span class=
=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"s1">'Python'</span><span class=3D"o">.</sp=
an><span class=3D"n">encode</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">type</span><span =
class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">encoded_str_to_bytes</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">&lt;class 'bytes'&gt;</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">encoded_str_to_byt=
es</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'Python'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.1: </span>A=
dded support for keyword arguments.</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.9: </span>T=
he value of the <em>errors</em> argument is now checked in <a class=3D"refe=
rence internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/devmode.html#devm=
ode"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Python Development Mode</span></a> and
in <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/using/=
configure.html#debug-build"><span class=3D"std std-ref">debug mode</span></=
a>.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.endswith">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">endswith</span><=
/span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=
=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">suffix</span></span></em><span class=3D"optional=
">[</span>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">s=
tart</span></span></em><span class=3D"optional">[</span>, <em class=3D"sig-=
param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">end</span></span></em><span cl=
ass=3D"optional">]</span><span class=3D"optional">]</span><span class=3D"si=
g-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/stdtypes.html#str.endswith" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=
=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">True</span></code> if the string ends with the specified <em>suffix</em=
>, otherwise return
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">False</spa=
n></code>.  <em>suffix</em> can also be a tuple of suffixes to look for.  W=
ith optional
<em>start</em>, test beginning at that position.  With optional <em>end</em=
>, stop comparing
at that position. Using <em>start</em> and <em>end</em> is equivalent to
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str[start:=
end].endswith(suffix)</span></code>. For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
