an class=3D"pre">**</span></span><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">kwar=
gs</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerli=
nk" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.format" tit=
le=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Perform a string formatting operation.  The string on which this met=
hod is
called can contain literal text or replacement fields delimited by braces
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">{}</span><=
/code>.  Each replacement field contains either the numeric index of a
positional argument, or the name of a keyword argument.  Returns a copy of
the string where each replacement field is replaced with the string value o=
f
the corresponding argument. For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-pycon notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"The sum of 1 + 2 is </span><span clas=
s=3D"si">{0}</span><span class=3D"s2">"</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">format</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">1<=
/span><span class=3D"o">+</span><span class=3D"mi">2</span><span class=3D"p=
">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'The sum of 1 + 2 is 3'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"The sum of </spa=
n><span class=3D"si">{a}</span><span class=3D"s2"> + </span><span class=3D"=
si">{b}</span><span class=3D"s2"> is </span><span class=3D"si">{answer}</sp=
an><span class=3D"s2">"</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">f=
ormat</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">answer</span><span =
class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"o">+</span>=
<span class=3D"mi">2</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">a</=
span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"=
p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">b</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span cla=
ss=3D"mi">2</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'The sum of 1 + 2 is 3'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"</span><span cla=
ss=3D"si">{1}</span><span class=3D"s2"> expects the </span><span class=3D"s=
i">{0}</span><span class=3D"s2"> Inquisition!"</span><span class=3D"o">.</s=
pan><span class=3D"n">format</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D=
"s2">"Spanish"</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s2">"Nobody"=
</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'Nobody expects the Spanish Inquisition!'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>See <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/string.html#formatstrings"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Format String =
Syntax</span></a> for a description of the various formatting options
that can be specified in format strings.</p>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>When formatting a number (<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https:=
//docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int" title=3D"int"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int<=
/span></code></a>, <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyt=
hon.org/3/library/functions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xref=
 py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span>=
</code></a>, <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/functions.html#complex" title=3D"complex"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">complex</span>=
</code></a>,
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/d=
ecimal.html#decimal.Decimal" title=3D"decimal.Decimal"><code class=3D"xref =
py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">decimal.Decim=
al</span></code></a> and subclasses) with the <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> type
(ex: <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'{:n}=
'.format(1234)</span></code>), the function temporarily sets the
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">LC_CTYPE</=
span></code> locale to the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><sp=
an class=3D"pre">LC_NUMERIC</span></code> locale to decode
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">decimal_po=
int</span></code> and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">thousands_sep</span></code> fields of <code class=3D"xref c c-f=
unc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">localeconv()</span></=
code> if
they are non-ASCII or longer than 1 byte, and the <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">LC_NUMERIC</span></code> locale is
different than the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">LC_CTYPE</span></code> locale.  This temporary change affects
other threads.</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.7: </span>W=
hen formatting a number with the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">n</span></code> type, the function sets
temporarily the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D=
"pre">LC_CTYPE</span></code> locale to the <code class=3D"docutils literal =
notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">LC_NUMERIC</span></code> locale in some
cases.</p>
</div>
