<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.isprintable">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">isprintable</spa=
n></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</spa=
n><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtype=
s.html#str.isprintable" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">True</span></code> if all characters in the string are printable, <code=
 class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">False</span></c=
ode> if it
contains at least one non-printable character.</p>
<p>Here =E2=80=9Cprintable=E2=80=9D means the character is suitable for <a =
class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/func=
tions.html#repr" title=3D"repr"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">repr()</span></code></a> to use in
its output; =E2=80=9Cnon-printable=E2=80=9D means that <a class=3D"referenc=
e internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#repr" =
title=3D"repr"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">repr()</span></code></a> on built-in types will
hex-escape the character.  It has no bearing on the handling of strings
written to <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/library/sys.html#sys.stdout" title=3D"sys.stdout"><code class=3D"xref py =
py-data docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.stdout</span>=
</code></a> or <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.=
org/3/library/sys.html#sys.stderr" title=3D"sys.stderr"><code class=3D"xref=
 py py-data docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.stderr</s=
pan></code></a>.</p>
<p>The printable characters are those which in the Unicode character databa=
se
(see <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libr=
ary/unicodedata.html#module-unicodedata" title=3D"unicodedata: Access the U=
nicode Database."><code class=3D"xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">unicodedata</span></code></a>) have a general catego=
ry in group Letter, Mark,
Number, Punctuation, or Symbol (L, M, N, P, or S); plus the ASCII space 0x2=
0.
Nonprintable characters are those in group Separator or Other (Z or C),
except the ASCII space.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-pycon notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">''</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">isprintable</span><span class=3D"p">(),</span> <span class=
=3D"s1">' '</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">isprintable</=
span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">(True, True)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span cla=
ss=3D"se">\t</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">isprintable</span><span class=3D"p">(),</span> <span class=
=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><spa=
n class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">isprintable</span><span class=3D"p"=
>()</span>
<span class=3D"go">(False, False)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

