an><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">dict</span=
></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"positional-only-separ=
ator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-only parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span=
 class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span=
><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes=
.html#str.maketrans" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py">
<em class=3D"property"><span class=3D"k"><span class=3D"pre">static</span><=
/span><span class=3D"w"> </span></em><span class=3D"sig-prename descclassna=
me"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"=
><span class=3D"pre">maketrans</span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</sp=
an><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">from</span=
></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre=
">to</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">remove=3D''</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span c=
lass=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren=
">)</span></dt>
<dd><p>This static method returns a translation table usable for <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.=
html#str.translate" title=3D"str.translate"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth =
docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str.translate()</span></c=
ode></a>.</p>
<p>If there is only one argument, it must be a dictionary mapping Unicode
ordinals (integers) or characters (strings of length 1) to Unicode ordinals=
,
strings (of arbitrary lengths) or <code class=3D"docutils literal notransla=
te"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code>.  Character keys will then be
converted to ordinals.</p>
<p>If there are two arguments, they must be strings of equal length, and in=
 the
resulting dictionary, each character in <em>from</em> will be mapped to the=
 character at
the same position in <em>to</em>.  If there is a third argument, it must be=
 a string,
whose characters will be mapped to <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code> in the result.</p>
</dd></dl>

