an><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D=
"n"><span class=3D"pre">sep</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span class=3D"p=
re">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre">None=
</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=
=3D"pre">maxsplit</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span class=3D"pre">=3D</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre">-1</span></spa=
n></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"ht=
tps://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.split" title=3D"Link to t=
his definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a list of the words in the string, using <em>sep</em> as the =
delimiter
string.  If <em>maxsplit</em> is given, at most <em>maxsplit</em> splits ar=
e done (thus,
the list will have at most <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><sp=
an class=3D"pre">maxsplit+1</span></code> elements).  If <em>maxsplit</em> =
is not
specified or <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">-1</span></code>, then there is no limit on the number of splits
(all possible splits are made).</p>
<p>If <em>sep</em> is given, consecutive delimiters are not grouped togethe=
r and are
deemed to delimit empty strings (for example, <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'1,,2'.split(',')</span></code> returns
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">['1',</spa=
n> <span class=3D"pre">'',</span> <span class=3D"pre">'2']</span></code>). =
 The <em>sep</em> argument may consist of multiple characters
as a single delimiter (to split with multiple delimiters, use
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/r=
e.html#re.split" title=3D"re.split"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils=
 literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">re.split()</span></code></a>). Sp=
litting an empty string with a specified separator
returns <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">['=
']</span></code>.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'1,2,3'</span><span class=3D"o">.</spa=
n><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1=
">','</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2', '3']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'1,2,3'</span><sp=
an class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</s=
pan><span class=3D"s1">','</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"=
n">maxsplit</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2,3']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'1,2,,3,'</span><=
span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(<=
/span><span class=3D"s1">','</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2', '', '3', '']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'1&lt;&gt;2&lt;&g=
t;3&lt;4'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><sp=
an class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'&lt;&gt;'</span><span class=3D"p=
">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2', '3&lt;4']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>If <em>sep</em> is not specified or is <code class=3D"docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code>, a different splitting a=
lgorithm is
applied: runs of consecutive whitespace are regarded as a single separator,
and the result will contain no empty strings at the start or end if the
string has leading or trailing whitespace.  Consequently, splitting an empt=
y
string or a string consisting of just whitespace with a <code class=3D"docu=
tils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code> separator
returns <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">[]=
</span></code>.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'1 2 3'</span><span class=3D"o">.</spa=
n><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2', '3']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'1 2 3'</span><sp=
an class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</s=
pan><span class=3D"n">maxsplit</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span clas=
s=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2 3']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'   1   2   3   '=
</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=
=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">['1', '2', '3']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>If <em>sep</em> is not specified or is <code class=3D"docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code> and  <em>maxsplit</em> i=
s <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">0</span>=
</code>, only
leading runs of consecutive whitespace are considered.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">""</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"kc">Non=
e</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=
=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">[]</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"   "</span><span=
 class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</spa=
n><span class=3D"kc">None</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"m=
i">0</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">[]</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"   foo   "</span=
><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">=
(</span><span class=3D"n">maxsplit</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span =
class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['foo   ']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>See also <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org=
/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.join" title=3D"str.join"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">join()</span></=
code></a>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method" id=3D"index-34">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.splitlines">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">splitlines</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span cla=
ss=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">keepends</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span =
class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D=
"pre">False</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D=
"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.sp=
litlines" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a list of the lines in the string, breaking at line boundarie=
s.  Line
breaks are not included in the resulting list unless <em>keepends</em> is g=
iven and
true.</p>
<p>This method splits on the following line boundaries.  In particular, the
boundaries are a superset of <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https:=
//docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-universal-newlines"><span class=3D"x=
ref std std-term">universal newlines</span></a>.</p>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Representation</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">\n</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Line Feed</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">\r</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Carriage Return</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">\r\n</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Carriage Return + Line Feed</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">\v</span></code> or <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">\x0b</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Line Tabulation</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">\f</span></code> or <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">\x0c</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Form Feed</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">\x1c</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>File Separator</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">\x1d</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Group Separator</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">\x1e</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Record Separator</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">\x85</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Next Line (C1 Control Code)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">\u2028</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Line Separator</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">\u2029</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Paragraph Separator</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.2: </span><=
code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">\v</span></=
code> and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
\f</span></code> added to list of line boundaries.</p>
</div>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'ab c</span><span class=3D"se">\n\n</s=
pan><span class=3D"s1">de fg</span><span class=3D"se">\r</span><span class=
=3D"s1">kl</span><span class=3D"se">\r\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><=
span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">splitlines</span><span class=3D"=
p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">['ab c', '', 'de fg', 'kl']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'ab c</span><span=
 class=3D"se">\n\n</span><span class=3D"s1">de fg</span><span class=3D"se">=
\r</span><span class=3D"s1">kl</span><span class=3D"se">\r\n</span><span cl=
ass=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">splitlines</=
span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">keepends</span><span class=
=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['ab c\n', '\n', 'de fg\r', 'kl\r\n']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>Unlike <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/stdtypes.html#str.split" title=3D"str.split"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">split()</span><=
/code></a> when a delimiter string <em>sep</em> is given, this
method returns an empty list for the empty string, and a terminal line
break does not result in an extra line:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">""</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">splitlines</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">[]</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"One line</span><=
span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s2">"</span><span class=3D"o">.</=
span><span class=3D"n">splitlines</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">['One line']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>For comparison, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">split('\n')</span></code> gives:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">''</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'</=
span><span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"=
p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'Two lines</span>=
<span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"o">.<=
/span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=
=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">['Two lines', '']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

