<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.strip">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">strip</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D=
"n"><span class=3D"pre">chars</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span class=3D=
"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=3D"pre">No=
ne</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"positional-on=
ly-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-only parameter separator (PEP 570=
)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren"=
>)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/=
stdtypes.html#str.strip" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the string with the leading and trailing characters=
 removed.
The <em>chars</em> argument is a string specifying the set of characters to=
 be removed.
If omitted or <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">None</span></code>, the <em>chars</em> argument defaults to removing wh=
itespace.
The <em>chars</em> argument is not a prefix or suffix; rather, all combinat=
ions of its
values are stripped:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'   spacious   '</span><span class=3D"=
o">.</span><span class=3D"n">strip</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">'spacious'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'www.example.com'=
</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">strip</span><span class=
=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'cmowz.'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'example'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The outermost leading and trailing <em>chars</em> argument values are st=
ripped
from the string. Characters are removed from the leading end until
reaching a string character that is not contained in the set of
characters in <em>chars</em>. A similar action takes place on the trailing =
end.
For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">comment_string</span> <span class=3D"o"=
>=3D</span> <span class=3D"s1">'#....... Section 3.2.1 Issue #32 .......'</=
span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">comment_string</sp=
an><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">strip</span><span class=3D"p=
">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'.#! '</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'Section 3.2.1 Issue #32'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

