<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.title">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">title</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a c=
lass=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html=
#str.title" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a titlecased version of the string where words start with an =
uppercase
character and the remaining characters are lowercase.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello world'</span><span class=3D"o">=
.</span><span class=3D"n">title</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">'Hello World'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The algorithm uses a simple language-independent definition of a word as
groups of consecutive letters.  The definition works in many contexts but
it means that apostrophes in contractions and possessives form word
boundaries, which may not be the desired result:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"they're bill's friends from the UK"</=
span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">title</span><span class=3D=
"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">"They'Re Bill'S Friends From The Uk"</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/string.html#string.capwords" title=3D"string.capwords"><code class=3D=
"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">string.c=
apwords()</span></code></a> function does not have this problem, as it
splits words on spaces only.</p>
<p>Alternatively, a workaround for apostrophes can be constructed using reg=
ular
expressions:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"kn">import</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"nn">re</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"k">def</span><span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">titlecase</span><span class=3D"p">(</s=
pan><span class=3D"n">s</span><span class=3D"p">):</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>    <span class=3D"k">return</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"n">re</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">sub</span><sp=
an class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"sa">r</span><span class=3D"s2">"[A-Za=
-z]+('[A-Za-z]+)?"</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>                  <span class=3D"k">lambda</s=
pan> <span class=3D"n">mo</span><span class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"n=
">mo</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">group</span><span cl=
ass=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><spa=
n class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">capitalize</span><span class=3D"p">=
(),</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>                  <span class=3D"n">s</span><=
span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">...</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">titlecase</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s2">"they're bill's friends."</span>=
<span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">"They're Bill's Friends."</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>See also <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org=
/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.istitle" title=3D"str.istitle"><code class=3D"=
xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">istitle()=
</span></code></a>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.translate">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">translate</span>=
</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span clas=
s=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">table</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-para=
m"><span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-on=
ly parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></span=
></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"htt=
ps://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.translate" title=3D"Link t=
o this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the string in which each character has been mapped =
through
the given translation table.  The table must be an object that implements
indexing via <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__getitem__" title=3D"object.__getitem_=
_"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">__getitem__()</span></code></a>, typically a <a class=3D"reference=
 internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-mapping"><s=
pan class=3D"xref std std-term">mapping</span></a> or
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.=
html#term-sequence"><span class=3D"xref std std-term">sequence</span></a>. =
 When indexed by a Unicode ordinal (an integer), the
table object can do any of the following: return a Unicode ordinal or a
string, to map the character to one or more other characters; return
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span=
></code>, to delete the character from the return string; or raise a
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/e=
xceptions.html#LookupError" title=3D"LookupError"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">LookupError</span></=
code></a> exception, to map the character to itself.</p>
<p>You can use <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.=
org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.maketrans" title=3D"str.maketrans"><code cl=
ass=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">st=
r.maketrans()</span></code></a> to create a translation map from
character-to-character mappings in different formats.</p>
<p>See also the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python=
.org/3/library/codecs.html#module-codecs" title=3D"codecs: Encode and decod=
e data and streams."><code class=3D"xref py py-mod docutils literal notrans=
late"><span class=3D"pre">codecs</span></code></a> module for a more flexib=
le approach to custom
character mappings.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.upper">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">upper</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a c=
lass=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html=
#str.upper" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the string with all the cased characters <a class=
=3D"footnote-reference brackets" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/=
stdtypes.html#id15" id=3D"id9" role=3D"doc-noteref"><span class=3D"fn-brack=
et">[</span>4<span class=3D"fn-bracket">]</span></a> converted to
uppercase.  Note that <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">s.upper().isupper()</span></code> might be <code class=3D"docut=
ils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">False</span></code> if <code c=
lass=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">s</span></code>
contains uncased characters or if the Unicode category of the resulting
character(s) is not =E2=80=9CLu=E2=80=9D (Letter, uppercase), but e.g. =E2=
=80=9CLt=E2=80=9D (Letter,
titlecase).</p>
<p>The uppercasing algorithm used is
<a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://www.unicode.org/versions/Un=
icode16.0.0/core-spec/chapter-3/#G33992">described in section 3.13 =E2=80=
=98Default Case Folding=E2=80=99 of the Unicode Standard</a>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"str.zfill">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">str.</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">zfill</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D=
"n"><span class=3D"pre">width</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param"><=
span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-only p=
arameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></span></e=
m><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https:/=
/docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.zfill" title=3D"Link to this d=
efinition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the string left filled with ASCII <code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'0'</span></code> digits to
make a string of length <em>width</em>. A leading sign prefix (<code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'+'</span></code>/<co=
de class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'-'</span></c=
ode>)
is handled by inserting the padding <em>after</em> the sign character rathe=
r
than before. The original string is returned if <em>width</em> is less than
or equal to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre=
">len(s)</span></code>.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"42"</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><=
span class=3D"n">zfill</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">5=
</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'00042'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"s2">"-42"</span><span=
 class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">zfill</span><span class=3D"p">(</spa=
n><span class=3D"mi">5</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'-0042'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

</section>
<section id=3D"formatted-string-literals-f-strings">
<span id=3D"stdtypes-fstrings"></span><span id=3D"index-35"></span><h3>Form=
atted String Literals (f-strings)<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://do=
cs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#formatted-string-literals-f-strings" =
title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.6.</span></p>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.7: </span>T=
he <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/refere=
nce/expressions.html#await"><code class=3D"xref std std-keyword docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">await</span></code></a> and <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/reference/compoun=
d_stmts.html#async-for"><code class=3D"xref std std-keyword docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">async</span> <span class=3D"pre">for</sp=
an></code></a> can be used in expressions
within f-strings.</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.8: </span>A=
dded the debug specifier (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><spa=
n class=3D"pre">=3D</span></code>)</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.12: </span>=
Many restrictions on expressions within f-strings have been removed.
Notably, nested strings, comments, and backslashes are now permitted.</p>
</div>
<p>An <em class=3D"dfn">f-string</em> (formally a <em class=3D"dfn">formatt=
ed string literal</em>) is
a string literal that is prefixed with <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">f</span></code> or <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">F</span></code>.
This type of string literal allows embedding the results of arbitrary Pytho=
n
expressions within <em>replacement fields</em>, which are delimited by curl=
y
brackets (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
{}</span></code>).
Each replacement field must contain an expression, optionally followed by:<=
/p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>a <em>debug specifier</em> =E2=80=93 an equal sign (<code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></code>);</p></l=
i>
<li><p>a <em>conversion specifier</em> =E2=80=93 <code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">!s</span></code>, <code class=3D"doc=
utils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">!r</span></code> or <code cl=
ass=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">!a</span></code>; =
and/or</p></li>
<li><p>a <em>format specifier</em> prefixed with a colon (<code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">:</span></code>).</p></li>
</ul>
<p>See the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/reference/lexical_analysis.html#f-strings"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Le=
xical Analysis section on f-strings</span></a> for details
on the syntax of these fields.</p>
<section id=3D"debug-specifier">
<h4>Debug specifier<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/library/stdtypes.html#debug-specifier" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=
=B6</a></h4>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.8.</span></p>
</div>
<p>If a debug specifier =E2=80=93 an equal sign (<code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></code>) =E2=80=93 appears=
 after the replacement
field expression, the resulting f-string will contain the expression=E2=80=
=99s source,
the equal sign, and the value of the expression.
This is often useful for debugging:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">number</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</sp=
an> <span class=3D"mf">14.3</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">number</span=
><span class=3D"si">=3D}</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'number=3D14.3'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>Whitespace before, inside and after the expression, as well as whitespac=
e
after the equal sign, is significant =E2=80=94 it is retained in the result=
:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><sp=
an class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">number<=
/span><span class=3D"w">  </span><span class=3D"o">-</span><span class=3D"w=
">  </span><span class=3D"mi">4</span><span class=3D"w">  </span><span clas=
s=3D"si">=3D }</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">' number  -  4  =3D 10.3'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"conversion-specifier">
<h4>Conversion specifier<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python=
.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#conversion-specifier" title=3D"Link to this he=
ading">=C2=B6</a></h4>
<p>By default, the value of a replacement field expression is converted to
a string using <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.=
org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-fu=
nc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str()</span></code></a=
>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"kn">from</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><=
span class=3D"nn">fractions</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"=
kn">import</span> <span class=3D"n">Fraction</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">one_third</span> <=
span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">Fraction</span><span class=3D=
"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"mi">3</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</s=
pan><span class=3D"si">}</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'1/3'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>When a debug specifier but no format specifier is used, the default conv=
ersion
instead uses <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/functions.html#repr" title=3D"repr"><code class=3D"xref py py-f=
unc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">repr()</span></code><=
/a>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><sp=
an class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</span><span class=3D"w"=
> </span><span class=3D"si">=3D }</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'one_third =3D Fraction(1, 3)'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The conversion can be specified explicitly using one of these specifiers=
:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">!s<=
/span></code> for <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyth=
on.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str()</span></code>=
</a></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">!r<=
/span></code> for <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyth=
on.org/3/library/functions.html#repr" title=3D"repr"><code class=3D"xref py=
 py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">repr()</span></c=
ode></a></p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">!a<=
/span></code> for <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyth=
on.org/3/library/functions.html#ascii" title=3D"ascii"><code class=3D"xref =
py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">ascii()</span>=
</code></a></p></li>
</ul>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">str</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><s=
pan class=3D"n">one_third</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">'1/3'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">repr</span><span =
class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</span><span class=3D"p">)</=
span>
<span class=3D"go">'Fraction(1, 3)'</span>

<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</s=
pan><span class=3D"si">!s}</span><span class=3D"s1"> is </span><span class=
=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</span><span class=3D"si">!r}</s=
pan><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'1/3 is Fraction(1, 3)'</span>

<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">string</span> <spa=
n class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"s2">"=C2=A1ko=C4=8Dka =F0=9F=98=B8!=
"</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">ascii</span><span =
class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">string</span><span class=3D"p">)</spa=
n>
<span class=3D"go">"'\\xa1ko\\u010dka \\U0001f638!'"</span>

<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">string</span=
><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"si">=3D !a}</span><span class=3D"=
s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">"string =3D '\\xa1ko\\u010dka \\U0001f638!'"</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"format-specifier">
<h4>Format specifier<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org=
/3/library/stdtypes.html#format-specifier" title=3D"Link to this heading">=
=C2=B6</a></h4>
<p>After the expression has been evaluated, and possibly converted using an
explicit conversion specifier, it is formatted using the <a class=3D"refere=
nce internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#form=
at" title=3D"format"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">format()</span></code></a> function.
If the replacement field includes a <em>format specifier</em> introduced by=
 a colon
(<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">:</span><=
/code>), the specifier is passed to <code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils=
 literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">format()</span></code> as the sec=
ond argument.
The result of <code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">format()</span></code> is then used as the final value =
for the
replacement field. For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"kn">from</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><=
span class=3D"nn">fractions</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"=
kn">import</span> <span class=3D"n">Fraction</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">one_third</span> <=
span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">Fraction</span><span class=3D=
"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"mi">3</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</s=
pan><span class=3D"si">:</span><span class=3D"s1">.6f</span><span class=3D"=
si">}</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'0.333333'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</s=
pan><span class=3D"si">:</span><span class=3D"s1">_^+10</span><span class=
=3D"si">}</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'___+1/3___'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"o">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span=
> <span class=3D"sa">f</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">=
{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</span><span class=3D"si">!r:</span><spa=
n class=3D"s1">_^20</span><span class=3D"si">}</span><span class=3D"s1">'</=
span>
<span class=3D"go">'___Fraction(1, 3)___'</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">f</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">{</span><span class=3D"n">one_third</s=
pan><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"si">=3D :</span><span class=3D=
"s1">~&gt;10</span><span class=3D"si">}</span><span class=3D"s1">~'</span>
<span class=3D"go">'one_third =3D ~~~~~~~1/3~'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</section>
</section>
<section id=3D"template-string-literals-t-strings">
<span id=3D"stdtypes-tstrings"></span><h3>Template String Literals (t-strin=
gs)<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtyp=
es.html#template-string-literals-t-strings" title=3D"Link to this heading">=
=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p>An <em class=3D"dfn">t-string</em> (formally a <em class=3D"dfn">templat=
e string literal</em>) is
a string literal that is prefixed with <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">t</span></code> or <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">T</span></code>.</p>
<p>These strings follow the same syntax and evaluation rules as
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tdtypes.html#stdtypes-fstrings"><span class=3D"std std-ref">formatted strin=
g literals</span></a>,
with for the following differences:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>Rather than evaluating to a <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">str</span></code> object, template string literals=
 evaluate
to a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libr=
ary/string.templatelib.html#string.templatelib.Template" title=3D"string.te=
mplatelib.Template"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">string.templatelib.Template</span></code></a> ob=
ject.</p></li>
<li><p>The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/library/functions.html#format" title=3D"format"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">format()</span></co=
de></a> protocol is not used.
Instead, the format specifier and conversions (if any) are passed to
a new <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/lib=
rary/string.templatelib.html#string.templatelib.Interpolation" title=3D"str=
ing.templatelib.Interpolation"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Interpolation</span></code></a> objec=
t that is created
for each evaluated expression.
It is up to code that processes the resulting <a class=3D"reference interna=
l" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/string.templatelib.html#string=
.templatelib.Template" title=3D"string.templatelib.Template"><code class=3D=
"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Templat=
e</span></code></a>
object to decide how to handle format specifiers and conversions.</p></li>
<li><p>Format specifiers containing nested replacement fields are evaluated=
 eagerly,
prior to being passed to the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https:=
//docs.python.org/3/library/string.templatelib.html#string.templatelib.Inte=
rpolation" title=3D"string.templatelib.Interpolation"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Interpolation<=
/span></code></a> object.
For instance, an interpolation of the form <code class=3D"docutils literal =
notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">{amount:.{precision}f}</span></code> will
evaluate the inner expression <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">{precision}</span></code> to determine the value of the
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">format_spe=
c</span></code> attribute.
If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">precisi=
on</span></code> were to be <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><s=
pan class=3D"pre">2</span></code>, the resulting format specifier
would be <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'=
.2f'</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>When the equals sign <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><s=
pan class=3D"pre">'=3D'</span></code> is provided in an interpolation expre=
ssion,
the text of the expression is appended to the literal string that precedes
the relevant interpolation.
This includes the equals sign and any surrounding whitespace.
The <code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">Interpolation</span></code> instance for the expression will be =
created as
normal, except that <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.py=
thon.org/3/library/string.templatelib.html#string.templatelib.Interpolation=
.conversion" title=3D"string.templatelib.Interpolation.conversion"><code cl=
ass=3D"xref py py-attr docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">co=
nversion</span></code></a> will
be set to =E2=80=98<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">r</span></code>=E2=80=99 (<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"=
https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#repr" title=3D"repr"><code=
 class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre"=
>repr()</span></code></a>) by default.
If an explicit conversion or format specifier are provided,
this will override the default behaviour.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id=3D"printf-style-string-formatting">
<span id=3D"old-string-formatting"></span><h3><code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">printf</span></code>-style String Forma=
tting<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdt=
ypes.html#printf-style-string-formatting" title=3D"Link to this heading">=
=C2=B6</a></h3>
<div class=3D"admonition note" id=3D"index-36">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>The formatting operations described here exhibit a variety of quirks tha=
t
lead to a number of common errors (such as failing to display tuples and
dictionaries correctly).</p>
<p>Using <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
reference/lexical_analysis.html#f-strings"><span class=3D"std std-ref">form=
atted string literals</span></a>, the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str.format" title=3D"st=
r.format"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><spa=
n class=3D"pre">str.format()</span></code></a>
interface, or <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.o=
rg/3/library/string.html#string.Template" title=3D"string.Template"><code c=
lass=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
string.Template</span></code></a> may help avoid these errors.
Each of these alternatives provides their own trade-offs and benefits of
simplicity, flexibility, and/or extensibility.</p>
</div>
<p>String objects have one unique built-in operation: the <code class=3D"do=
cutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%</span></code> operator (m=
odulo).
This is also known as the string <em>formatting</em> or <em>interpolation</=
em> operator.
Given <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">form=
at</span> <span class=3D"pre">%</span> <span class=3D"pre">values</span></c=
ode> (where <em>format</em> is a string), <code class=3D"docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%</span></code> conversion
specifications in <em>format</em> are replaced with zero or more elements o=
f <em>values</em>.
The effect is similar to using the <code class=3D"xref c c-func docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sprintf()</span></code> function in =
the C language.
For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-pycon notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">print</span><span class=3D"p">(</span>=
<span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">%s</span><span class=3D"s1"> =
has </span><span class=3D"si">%d</span><span class=3D"s1"> quote types.'</s=
pan> <span class=3D"o">%</span> <span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s1=
">'Python'</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"mi">2</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">))</span>
<span class=3D"go">Python has 2 quote types.</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>If <em>format</em> requires a single argument, <em>values</em> may be a =
single non-tuple
object. <a class=3D"footnote-reference brackets" href=3D"https://docs.pytho=
n.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#id16" id=3D"id10" role=3D"doc-noteref"><span =
class=3D"fn-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"fn-bracket">]</span></a>  Othe=
rwise, <em>values</em> must be a tuple with exactly the number of
items specified by the format string, or a single mapping object (for examp=
le, a
dictionary).</p>
<p id=3D"index-37">A conversion specifier contains two or more characters a=
nd has the following
components, which must occur in this order:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple">
<li><p>The <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre"=
>'%'</span></code> character, which marks the start of the specifier.</p></=
li>
<li><p>Mapping key (optional), consisting of a parenthesised sequence of ch=
aracters
(for example, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">(somename)</span></code>).</p></li>
<li><p>Conversion flags (optional), which affect the result of some convers=
ion
types.</p></li>
<li><p>Minimum field width (optional).  If specified as an <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'*'</span></code> (asteris=
k), the
actual width is read from the next element of the tuple in <em>values</em>,=
 and the
object to convert comes after the minimum field width and optional precisio=
n.</p></li>
<li><p>Precision (optional), given as a <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'.'</span></code> (dot) followed by the preci=
sion.  If
specified as <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">'*'</span></code> (an asterisk), the actual precision is read from the n=
ext
element of the tuple in <em>values</em>, and the value to convert comes aft=
er the
precision.</p></li>
<li><p>Length modifier (optional).</p></li>
<li><p>Conversion type.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>When the right argument is a dictionary (or other mapping type), then th=
e
formats in the string <em>must</em> include a parenthesised mapping key int=
o that
dictionary inserted immediately after the <code class=3D"docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'%'</span></code> character. The mapping ke=
y
selects the value to be formatted from the mapping.  For example:</p>
<div class=3D"doctest highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highligh=
t" style=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"butto=
n" title=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=
=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">print</span><span class=3D"p=
">(</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"si">%(language)s</span>=
<span class=3D"s1"> has </span><span class=3D"si">%(number)03d</span><span =
class=3D"s1"> quote types.'</span> <span class=3D"o">%</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>      <span class=3D"p">{</span><span class=
=3D"s1">'language'</span><span class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"s2">"Pyt=
hon"</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s2">"number"</span><sp=
an class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"mi">2</span><span class=3D"p">})</sp=
an>
<span class=3D"go">Python has 002 quote types.</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>In this case no <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">*</span></code> specifiers may occur in a format (since they requi=
re a
sequential parameter list).</p>
<p>The conversion flag characters are:</p>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault" id=3D"index-38">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Flag</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'#'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>The value conversion will use the =E2=80=9Calternate form=E2=80=9D (=
where defined
below).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'0'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>The conversion will be zero padded for numeric values.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'-'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>The converted value is left adjusted (overrides the <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'0'</span></code>
conversion if both are given).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'</span> <span class=3D"pre">'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>(a space) A blank should be left before a positive number (or empty
string) produced by a signed conversion.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'+'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>A sign character (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">'+'</span></code> or <code class=3D"docutils literal notrans=
late"><span class=3D"pre">'-'</span></code>) will precede the conversion
(overrides a =E2=80=9Cspace=E2=80=9D flag).</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>A length modifier (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">h</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">l</span></code>, or <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">L</span></code>) may be present, but is ignore=
d as it
is not necessary for Python =E2=80=93 so e.g. <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%ld</span></code> is identical to <code=
 class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%d</span></code=
>.</p>
<p>The conversion types are:</p>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Conversion</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'d'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed integer decimal.</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'i'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed integer decimal.</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'o'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed octal value.</p></td>
<td><p>(1)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'u'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Obsolete type =E2=80=93 it is identical to <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'d'</span></code>.</p></td>
<td><p>(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'x'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed hexadecimal (lowercase).</p></td>
<td><p>(2)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'X'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed hexadecimal (uppercase).</p></td>
<td><p>(2)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'e'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Floating-point exponential format (lowercase).</p></td>
<td><p>(3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'E'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Floating-point exponential format (uppercase).</p></td>
<td><p>(3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'f'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Floating-point decimal format.</p></td>
<td><p>(3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'F'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Floating-point decimal format.</p></td>
<td><p>(3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'g'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Floating-point format. Uses lowercase exponential
format if exponent is less than -4 or not less than
precision, decimal format otherwise.</p></td>
<td><p>(4)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'G'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Floating-point format. Uses uppercase exponential
format if exponent is less than -4 or not less than
precision, decimal format otherwise.</p></td>
<td><p>(4)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'c'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Single character (accepts integer or single
character string).</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'r'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>String (converts any Python object using
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#repr" title=3D"repr"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">repr()</span></code></a>).</p></td=
>
<td><p>(5)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'s'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>String (converts any Python object using
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str()</span></code></a>).</p></td>
<td><p>(5)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'a'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>String (converts any Python object using
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#ascii" title=3D"ascii"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">ascii()</span></code></a>).</p><=
/td>
<td><p>(5)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'%'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>No argument is converted, results in a <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'%'</span></code>
character in the result.</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic">
<li><p>The alternate form causes a leading octal specifier (<code class=3D"=
docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'0o'</span></code>) to be
inserted before the first digit.</p></li>
<li><p>The alternate form causes a leading <code class=3D"docutils literal =
notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'0x'</span></code> or <code class=3D"docut=
ils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'0X'</span></code> (depending =
on whether
the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'x'</s=
pan></code> or <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"=
pre">'X'</span></code> format was used) to be inserted before the first dig=
it.</p></li>
<li><p>The alternate form causes the result to always contain a decimal poi=
nt, even if
no digits follow it.</p>
<p>The precision determines the number of digits after the decimal point an=
d
defaults to 6.</p>
</li>
<li><p>The alternate form causes the result to always contain a decimal poi=
nt, and
trailing zeroes are not removed as they would otherwise be.</p>
<p>The precision determines the number of significant digits before and aft=
er the
decimal point and defaults to 6.</p>
</li>
<li><p>If precision is <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">N</span></code>, the output is truncated to <code class=3D"doc=
utils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">N</span></code> characters.<=
/p></li>
<li><p>See <span class=3D"target" id=3D"index-39"></span><a class=3D"pep re=
ference external" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0237/"><strong>PEP 23=
7</strong></a>.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Since Python strings have an explicit length, <code class=3D"docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%s</span></code> conversions do not =
assume
that <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'\0'<=
/span></code> is the end of the string.</p>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.1: </span><=
code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%f</span></=
code> conversions for numbers whose absolute value is over 1e50 are no
longer replaced by <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">%g</span></code> conversions.</p>
</div>
</section>
