<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"bytes.expandtabs">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">bytes.</span>=
</span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">expandtabs</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><span c=
lass=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">tabsize</span></span><span class=3D"o"><span=
 class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span class=
=3D"pre">8</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"=
headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes.e=
xpandtabs" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"bytearray.expandtabs">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray.</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">expandtabs=
</span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><sp=
an class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">tabsize</span></span><span class=3D"o"><=
span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">8</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=
=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#byt=
earray.expandtabs" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the sequence where all ASCII tab characters are rep=
laced
by one or more ASCII spaces, depending on the current column and the given
tab size.  Tab positions occur every <em>tabsize</em> bytes (default is 8,
giving tab positions at columns 0, 8, 16 and so on).  To expand the
sequence, the current column is set to zero and the sequence is examined
byte by byte.  If the byte is an ASCII tab character (<code class=3D"docuti=
ls literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">b'\t'</span></code>), one or
more space characters are inserted in the result until the current column
is equal to the next tab position. (The tab character itself is not
copied.)  If the current byte is an ASCII newline (<code class=3D"docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">b'\n'</span></code>) or
carriage return (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">b'\r'</span></code>), it is copied and the current column is reset
to zero.  Any other byte value is copied unchanged and the current column
is incremented by one regardless of how the byte value is represented when
printed:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'01</span><=
span class=3D"se">\t</span><span class=3D"s1">012</span><span class=3D"se">=
\t</span><span class=3D"s1">0123</span><span class=3D"se">\t</span><span cl=
ass=3D"s1">01234'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">expandt=
abs</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'01      012     0123    01234'</span>
