pan></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">splitlines=
</span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=3D"sig-param"><sp=
an class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">keepends</span></span><span class=3D"o">=
<span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"default_value"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">False</span></span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a cl=
ass=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#=
bytearray.splitlines" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a list of the lines in the binary sequence, breaking at ASCII
line boundaries. This method uses the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-universal-newlines"><span =
class=3D"xref std std-term">universal newlines</span></a> approach
to splitting lines. Line breaks are not included in the resulting list
unless <em>keepends</em> is given and true.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'ab c</span=
><span class=3D"se">\n\n</span><span class=3D"s1">de fg</span><span class=
=3D"se">\r</span><span class=3D"s1">kl</span><span class=3D"se">\r\n</span>=
<span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">spli=
tlines</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">[b'ab c', b'', b'de fg', b'kl']</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s1">'ab c</span><span class=3D"se">\n\n</span><span class=3D"s1">de f=
g</span><span class=3D"se">\r</span><span class=3D"s1">kl</span><span class=
=3D"se">\r\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><sp=
an class=3D"n">splitlines</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n"=
>keepends</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span><=
span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">[b'ab c\n', b'\n', b'de fg\r', b'kl\r\n']</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>Unlike <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/stdtypes.html#bytes.split" title=3D"bytes.split"><code class=3D"xr=
ef py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">split()</sp=
an></code></a> when a delimiter string <em>sep</em> is given, this
method returns an empty list for the empty string, and a terminal line
break does not result in an extra line:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s2">""</span><s=
pan class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</=
span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"s=
e">\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"p">),</span> <span cl=
ass=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s2">"Two lines</span><span class=3D"se">\=
n</span><span class=3D"s2">"</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D=
"n">split</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span =
class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span=
><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">([b''], [b'Two lines', b''])</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span cla=
ss=3D"s2">""</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">splitlines</=
span><span class=3D"p">(),</span> <span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D=
"s2">"One line</span><span class=3D"se">\n</span><span class=3D"s2">"</span=
><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">splitlines</span><span class=
=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">([], [b'One line'])</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"bytes.swapcase">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">bytes.</span>=
</span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">swapcase</span=
></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span=
><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes=
.html#bytes.swapcase" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"bytearray.swapcase">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray.</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">swapcase</=
span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</=
span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdt=
ypes.html#bytearray.swapcase" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a><=
/dt>
<dd><p>Return a copy of the sequence with all the lowercase ASCII character=
s
converted to their corresponding uppercase counterpart and vice-versa.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello Worl=
d'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">swapcase</span><span c=
lass=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'hELLO wORLD'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>Lowercase ASCII characters are those byte values in the sequence
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">b'abcdefgh=
ijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'</span></code>. Uppercase ASCII characters
are those byte values in the sequence <code class=3D"docutils literal notra=
nslate"><span class=3D"pre">b'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'</span></code>.</p=
>
<p>Unlike <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/stdtypes.html#str.swapcase" title=3D"str.swapcase"><code class=3D"=
xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str.swapc=
ase()</span></code></a>, it is always the case that
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bin.swapca=
se().swapcase()</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre=
">bin</span></code> for the binary versions. Case
conversions are symmetrical in ASCII, even though that is not generally
true for arbitrary Unicode code points.</p>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>The bytearray version of this method does <em>not</em> operate in place =
- it
always produces a new object, even if no changes were made.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"bytes.title">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">bytes.</span>=
</span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">title</span></=
span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a=
 class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.ht=
ml#bytes.title" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"bytearray.title">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray.</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">title</spa=
n></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</spa=
n><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtype=
s.html#bytearray.title" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a titlecased version of the binary sequence where words start=
 with
an uppercase ASCII character and the remaining characters are lowercase.
Uncased byte values are left unmodified.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'Hello worl=
d'</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">title</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'Hello World'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>Lowercase ASCII characters are those byte values in the sequence
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">b'abcdefgh=
ijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'</span></code>. Uppercase ASCII characters
are those byte values in the sequence <code class=3D"docutils literal notra=
nslate"><span class=3D"pre">b'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'</span></code>.
All other byte values are uncased.</p>
<p>The algorithm uses a simple language-independent definition of a word as
groups of consecutive letters.  The definition works in many contexts but
it means that apostrophes in contractions and possessives form word
boundaries, which may not be the desired result:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s2">"they're bi=
ll's friends from the UK"</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n"=
>title</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"go">b"They'Re Bill'S Friends From The Uk"</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>A workaround for apostrophes can be constructed using regular expression=
s:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"kn">import</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"nn">re</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"k">def</span><span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">titlecase</span><span class=3D"p">(</s=
pan><span class=3D"n">s</span><span class=3D"p">):</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>    <span class=3D"k">return</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"n">re</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">sub</span><sp=
an class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"sa">rb</span><span class=3D"s2">"[A-Z=
a-z]+('[A-Za-z]+)?"</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>                  <span class=3D"k">lambda</s=
pan> <span class=3D"n">mo</span><span class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"n=
">mo</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">group</span><span cl=
ass=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">)[</span><sp=
an class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">:</span><span class=3D"mi">1</spa=
n><span class=3D"p">]</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">upp=
er</span><span class=3D"p">()</span> <span class=3D"o">+</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>                             <span class=3D"n=
">mo</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">group</span><span cl=
ass=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">)[</span><sp=
an class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">:]</span><span class=3D"o">.</spa=
n><span class=3D"n">lower</span><span class=3D"p">(),</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>                  <span class=3D"n">s</span><=
span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">...</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">titlecase</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s2">"they=
're bill's friends."</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"go">b"They're Bill's Friends."</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>The bytearray version of this method does <em>not</em> operate in place =
- it
always produces a new object, even if no changes were made.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

