<section id=3D"printf-style-bytes-formatting">
<span id=3D"bytes-formatting"></span><h3><code class=3D"docutils literal no=
translate"><span class=3D"pre">printf</span></code>-style Bytes Formatting<=
a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.h=
tml#printf-style-bytes-formatting" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a=
></h3>
<div class=3D"admonition note" id=3D"index-46">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>The formatting operations described here exhibit a variety of quirks tha=
t
lead to a number of common errors (such as failing to display tuples and
dictionaries correctly).  If the value being printed may be a tuple or
dictionary, wrap it in a tuple.</p>
</div>
<p>Bytes objects (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">bytes</span></code>/<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">bytearray</span></code>) have one unique built-in operat=
ion:
the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%</spa=
n></code> operator (modulo).
This is also known as the bytes <em>formatting</em> or <em>interpolation</e=
m> operator.
Given <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">form=
at</span> <span class=3D"pre">%</span> <span class=3D"pre">values</span></c=
ode> (where <em>format</em> is a bytes object), <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%</span></code> conversion
specifications in <em>format</em> are replaced with zero or more elements o=
f <em>values</em>.
The effect is similar to using the <code class=3D"xref c c-func docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sprintf()</span></code> in the C lan=
guage.</p>
<p>If <em>format</em> requires a single argument, <em>values</em> may be a =
single non-tuple
object. <a class=3D"footnote-reference brackets" href=3D"https://docs.pytho=
n.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#id16" id=3D"id11" role=3D"doc-noteref"><span =
class=3D"fn-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"fn-bracket">]</span></a>  Othe=
rwise, <em>values</em> must be a tuple with exactly the number of
items specified by the format bytes object, or a single mapping object (for
example, a dictionary).</p>
<p id=3D"index-47">A conversion specifier contains two or more characters a=
nd has the following
components, which must occur in this order:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple">
<li><p>The <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre"=
>'%'</span></code> character, which marks the start of the specifier.</p></=
li>
<li><p>Mapping key (optional), consisting of a parenthesised sequence of ch=
aracters
(for example, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">(somename)</span></code>).</p></li>
<li><p>Conversion flags (optional), which affect the result of some convers=
ion
types.</p></li>
<li><p>Minimum field width (optional).  If specified as an <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'*'</span></code> (asteris=
k), the
actual width is read from the next element of the tuple in <em>values</em>,=
 and the
object to convert comes after the minimum field width and optional precisio=
n.</p></li>
<li><p>Precision (optional), given as a <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'.'</span></code> (dot) followed by the preci=
sion.  If
specified as <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">'*'</span></code> (an asterisk), the actual precision is read from the n=
ext
element of the tuple in <em>values</em>, and the value to convert comes aft=
er the
precision.</p></li>
<li><p>Length modifier (optional).</p></li>
<li><p>Conversion type.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>When the right argument is a dictionary (or other mapping type), then th=
e
formats in the bytes object <em>must</em> include a parenthesised mapping k=
ey into that
dictionary inserted immediately after the <code class=3D"docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'%'</span></code> character. The mapping ke=
y
selects the value to be formatted from the mapping.  For example:</p>
<div class=3D"doctest highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highligh=
t" style=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"butto=
n" title=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=
=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">print</span><span class=3D"p=
">(</span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'</span><span class=
=3D"si">%(language)s</span><span class=3D"s1"> has </span><span class=3D"si=
">%(number)03d</span><span class=3D"s1"> quote types.'</span> <span class=
=3D"o">%</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>      <span class=3D"p">{</span><span class=
=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'language'</span><span class=3D"p">:</sp=
an> <span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s2">"Python"</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s2">"number"</sp=
an><span class=3D"p">:</span> <span class=3D"mi">2</span><span class=3D"p">=
})</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'Python has 002 quote types.'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>In this case no <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">*</span></code> specifiers may occur in a format (since they requi=
re a
sequential parameter list).</p>
<p>The conversion flag characters are:</p>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault" id=3D"index-48">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Flag</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'#'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>The value conversion will use the =E2=80=9Calternate form=E2=80=9D (=
where defined
below).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'0'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>The conversion will be zero padded for numeric values.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'-'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>The converted value is left adjusted (overrides the <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">'0'</span></code>
conversion if both are given).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'</span> <span class=3D"pre">'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>(a space) A blank should be left before a positive number (or empty
string) produced by a signed conversion.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'+'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>A sign character (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">'+'</span></code> or <code class=3D"docutils literal notrans=
late"><span class=3D"pre">'-'</span></code>) will precede the conversion
(overrides a =E2=80=9Cspace=E2=80=9D flag).</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>A length modifier (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">h</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">l</span></code>, or <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">L</span></code>) may be present, but is ignore=
d as it
is not necessary for Python =E2=80=93 so e.g. <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%ld</span></code> is identical to <code=
 class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">%d</span></code=
>.</p>
<p>The conversion types are:</p>
<div class=3D"responsive-table__container"><table class=3D"docutils align-d=
efault">
<thead>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><th class=3D"head"><p>Conversion</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"head"><p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">'d'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed integer decimal.</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-odd"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">'i'</span></code></p></td>
<td><p>Signed integer decimal.</p></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"row-even"><td><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
