<section id=3D"memory-views">
<span id=3D"typememoryview"></span><h3>Memory Views<a class=3D"headerlink" =
href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#memory-views" title=
=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/librar=
y/stdtypes.html#memoryview" title=3D"memoryview"><code class=3D"xref py py-=
class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">memoryview</span></=
code></a> objects allow Python code to access the internal data
of an object that supports the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/c-api/buffer.html#bufferobjects"><span class=3D"std s=
td-ref">buffer protocol</span></a> without
copying.</p>
<dl class=3D"py class">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"memoryview">
<em class=3D"property"><span class=3D"k"><span class=3D"pre">class</span></=
span><span class=3D"w"> </span></em><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span=
 class=3D"pre">memoryview</span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><e=
m class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">object</span></=
span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D=
"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#memoryview" title=3D"Link =
to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><blockquote>
<div><p>Create a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pytho=
n.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#memoryview" title=3D"memoryview"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">memo=
ryview</span></code></a> that references <em>object</em>.  <em>object</em> =
must
support the buffer protocol.  Built-in objects that support the buffer
protocol include <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pytho=
n.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><code class=3D"xref py=
 py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes</span></c=
ode></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytearray" title=3D"bytearray"><code class=3D"xre=
f py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray</=
span></code></a>.</p>
<p>A <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libr=
ary/stdtypes.html#memoryview" title=3D"memoryview"><code class=3D"xref py p=
y-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">memoryview</span>=
</code></a> has the notion of an <em>element</em>, which is the
atomic memory unit handled by the originating <em>object</em>.  For many si=
mple
types such as <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.o=
rg/3/library/stdtypes.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes</span></code=
></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3=
/library/stdtypes.html#bytearray" title=3D"bytearray"><code class=3D"xref p=
y py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray</spa=
n></code></a>, an element is a single
byte, but other types such as <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https=
://docs.python.org/3/library/array.html#array.array" title=3D"array.array">=
<code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">array.array</span></code></a> may have bigger elements.</p>
<p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">len(vie=
w)</span></code> is equal to the length of <a class=3D"reference internal" =
href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#memoryview.tolist" =
title=3D"memoryview.tolist"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tolist</span></code></a>, which
is the nested list representation of the view. If <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">view.ndim</span> <span class=3D"pre=
">=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">1</span></code>,
this is equal to the number of elements in the view.</p>
<div class=3D"versionchanged">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified changed">Changed in version 3.12: </span>=
If <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">view.nd=
im</span> <span class=3D"pre">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">0</span></c=
ode>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">len(=
view)</span></code> now raises <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#TypeError" title=3D"TypeError=
"><code class=3D"xref py py-exc docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">TypeError</span></code></a> instead of returning 1.</p>
</div>
<p>The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/stdtypes.html#memoryview.itemsize" title=3D"memoryview.itemsize"><cod=
e class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">itemsize</span></code></a> attribute will give you the number of
bytes in a single element.</p>
<p>A <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libr=
ary/stdtypes.html#memoryview" title=3D"memoryview"><code class=3D"xref py p=
y-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">memoryview</span>=
</code></a> supports slicing and indexing to expose its data.
One-dimensional slicing will result in a subview:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">v</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <=
span class=3D"nb">memoryview</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D=
"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'abcefg'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">v</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"go">98</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">v</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"o">-</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span =
class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"go">103</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">v</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">:</span><span =
class=3D"mi">4</span><span class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"go">&lt;memory at 0x7f3ddc9f4350&gt;</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">bytes</span><span=
 class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">v</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><s=
pan class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">:</span><span class=3D"mi">4</sp=
an><span class=3D"p">])</span>
<span class=3D"go">b'bce'</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>If <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/lib=
rary/stdtypes.html#memoryview.format" title=3D"memoryview.format"><code cla=
ss=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">fo=
rmat</span></code></a> is one of the native format specifiers
from the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/struct.html#module-struct" title=3D"struct: Interpret bytes as pack=
ed binary data."><code class=3D"xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">struct</span></code></a> module, indexing with an int=
eger or a tuple of
