<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"memoryview.release">
<span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">release</span></span>=
<span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a clas=
s=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#me=
moryview.release" title=3D"Link to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Release the underlying buffer exposed by the memoryview object.  Man=
y
objects take special actions when a view is held on them (for example,
a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library=
/stdtypes.html#bytearray" title=3D"bytearray"><code class=3D"xref py py-cla=
ss docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytearray</span></code=
></a> would temporarily forbid resizing); therefore,
calling release() is handy to remove these restrictions (and free any
dangling resources) as soon as possible.</p>
<p>After this method has been called, any further operation on the view
raises a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/exceptions.html#ValueError" title=3D"ValueError"><code class=3D"xre=
f py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">ValueError<=
/span></code></a> (except <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://d=
ocs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#memoryview.release" title=3D"memoryv=
iew.release"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">release()</span></code></a> itself which can
be called multiple times):</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">m</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <=
span class=3D"nb">memoryview</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D=
"sa">b</span><span class=3D"s1">'abc'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">m</span><span clas=
s=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">release</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">m</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"gt">Traceback (most recent call last):</span>
  File <span class=3D"nb">"&lt;stdin&gt;"</span>, line <span class=3D"m">1<=
/span>, in <span class=3D"n">&lt;module&gt;</span>
<span class=3D"gr">ValueError</span>: <span class=3D"n">operation forbidden=
 on released memoryview object</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The context management protocol can be used for a similar effect,
using the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
with</span></code> statement:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"k">with</span> <span class=3D"nb">memoryvi=
ew</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"sa">b</span><span class=
=3D"s1">'abc'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"k">as</span> =
<span class=3D"n">m</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
<span class=3D"gp">... </span>    <span class=3D"n">m</span><span class=3D"=
p">[</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"gp">...</span>
<span class=3D"go">97</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">m</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"gt">Traceback (most recent call last):</span>
  File <span class=3D"nb">"&lt;stdin&gt;"</span>, line <span class=3D"m">1<=
/span>, in <span class=3D"n">&lt;module&gt;</span>
<span class=3D"gr">ValueError</span>: <span class=3D"n">operation forbidden=
 on released memoryview object</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.2.</span></p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

