<section id=3D"set-types-set-frozenset">
<span id=3D"types-set"></span><h2>Set Types =E2=80=94 <a class=3D"reference=
 internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#set" tit=
le=3D"set"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><s=
pan class=3D"pre">set</span></code></a>, <a class=3D"reference internal" hr=
ef=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#frozenset" title=3D"f=
rozenset"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><sp=
an class=3D"pre">frozenset</span></code></a><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D=
"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#set-types-set-frozenset" t=
itle=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h2>
<p id=3D"index-52">A <em class=3D"dfn">set</em> object is an unordered coll=
ection of distinct <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.pyt=
hon.org/3/glossary.html#term-hashable"><span class=3D"xref std std-term">ha=
shable</span></a> objects.
Common uses include membership testing, removing duplicates from a sequence=
, and
computing mathematical operations such as intersection, union, difference, =
and
symmetric difference.
(For other containers see the built-in <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#dict" title=3D"dict"><c=
ode class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"=
pre">dict</span></code></a>, <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https:=
//docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#list" title=3D"list"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">list=
</span></code></a>,
and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/stdtypes.html#tuple" title=3D"tuple"><code class=3D"xref py py-class doc=
utils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tuple</span></code></a> clas=
ses, and the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/collections.html#module-collections" title=3D"collections: Cont=
ainer datatypes"><code class=3D"xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">collections</span></code></a> module.)</p>
<p>Like other collections, sets support <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=3D"pre">in</span> <span =
class=3D"pre">set</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">len(set)</span></code>, and <code class=3D"docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">for</span> <span class=3D"pre">x</=
span> <span class=3D"pre">in</span>
<span class=3D"pre">set</span></code>.  Being an unordered collection, sets=
 do not record element position or
order of insertion.  Accordingly, sets do not support indexing, slicing, or
other sequence-like behavior.</p>
<p>There are currently two built-in set types, <a class=3D"reference intern=
al" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#set" title=3D"s=
et"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">set</span></code></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#frozenset" title=3D"fro=
zenset"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">frozenset</span></code></a>.
The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/stdtypes.html#set" title=3D"set"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">set</span></code></a> type is mu=
table =E2=80=94 the contents can be changed using methods
like <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libr=
ary/stdtypes.html#set.add" title=3D"set.add"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth=
 docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">add()</span></code></a> =
and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/stdtypes.html#set.remove" title=3D"set.remove"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">remove()</span></co=
de></a>.
Since it is mutable, it has no hash value and cannot be used as
either a dictionary key or as an element of another set.
The <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/stdtypes.html#frozenset" title=3D"frozenset"><code class=3D"xref py py-c=
lass docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">frozenset</span></co=
de></a> type is immutable and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https=
://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-hashable"><span class=3D"xref std s=
td-term">hashable</span></a> =E2=80=94
its contents cannot be altered after it is created;
it can therefore be used as a dictionary key or as an element of another se=
t.</p>
<p>Non-empty sets (not frozensets) can be created by placing a comma-separa=
ted list
of elements within braces, for example: <code class=3D"docutils literal not=
ranslate"><span class=3D"pre">{'jack',</span> <span class=3D"pre">'sjoerd'}=
</span></code>, in addition to the
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
tdtypes.html#set" title=3D"set"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils li=
teral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">set</span></code></a> constructor.</=
p>
<p>The constructors for both classes work the same:</p>
<dl class=3D"py class">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"set">
<em class=3D"property"><span class=3D"k"><span class=3D"pre">class</span></=
span><span class=3D"w"> </span></em><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span=
 class=3D"pre">set</span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em class=
=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">iterable</span></span>=
<span class=3D"o"><span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D"defau=
lt_value"><span class=3D"pre">()</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig-param=
"><span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Positional-onl=
y parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr></span>=
</em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#set" title=3D"Link to this defi=
nition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"frozenset">
<em class=3D"property"><span class=3D"k"><span class=3D"pre">class</span></=
span><span class=3D"w"> </span></em><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span=
 class=3D"pre">frozenset</span></span><span class=3D"sig-paren">(</span><em=
 class=3D"sig-param"><span class=3D"n"><span class=3D"pre">iterable</span><=
/span><span class=3D"o"><span class=3D"pre">=3D</span></span><span class=3D=
"default_value"><span class=3D"pre">()</span></span></em>, <em class=3D"sig=
-param"><span class=3D"positional-only-separator o"><abbr title=3D"Position=
al-only parameter separator (PEP 570)"><span class=3D"pre">/</span></abbr><=
/span></em><span class=3D"sig-paren">)</span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#frozenset" title=3D"Lin=
k to this definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>Return a new set or frozenset object whose elements are taken from
<em>iterable</em>.  The elements of a set must be <a class=3D"reference int=
ernal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-hashable"><span=
 class=3D"xref std std-term">hashable</span></a>.  To
represent sets of sets, the inner sets must be <a class=3D"reference intern=
al" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#frozenset" titl=
e=3D"frozenset"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">frozenset</span></code></a>
objects.  If <em>iterable</em> is not specified, a new empty set is
returned.</p>
</dd></dl>

<p>Sets can be created by several means:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>Use a comma-separated list of elements within braces: <code class=3D=
"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">{'jack',</span> <span cl=
ass=3D"pre">'sjoerd'}</span></code></p></li>
<li><p>Use a set comprehension: <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">{c</span> <span class=3D"pre">for</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">c</span> <span class=3D"pre">in</span> <span class=3D"pre">'abraca=
dabra'</span> <span class=3D"pre">if</span> <span class=3D"pre">c</span> <s=
pan class=3D"pre">not</span> <span class=3D"pre">in</span> <span class=3D"p=
re">'abc'}</span></code></p></li>
<li><p>Use the type constructor: <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">set()</span></code>, <code class=3D"docutils literal=
 notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">set('foobar')</span></code>, <code class=
=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">set(['a',</span> <spa=
n class=3D"pre">'b',</span> <span class=3D"pre">'foo'])</span></code></p></=
li>
</ul>
<p>Instances of <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python=
.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#set" title=3D"set"><code class=3D"xref py py-c=
lass docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">set</span></code></a=
> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/lib=
rary/stdtypes.html#frozenset" title=3D"frozenset"><code class=3D"xref py py=
-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">frozenset</span></=
code></a> provide the following
operations:</p>
<dl class=3D"describe">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object">
<span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">len(s)</span></span><=
/dt>
<dd><p>Return the number of elements in set <em>s</em> (cardinality of <em>=
s</em>).</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"describe">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object">
<span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">in</span> <span class=3D"pre">s</span></span></dt>
<dd><p>Test <em>x</em> for membership in <em>s</em>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"describe">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object">
<span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">x</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">not</span> <span class=3D"pre">in</span> <span class=3D"pre">s</sp=
an></span></dt>
<dd><p>Test <em>x</em> for non-membership in <em>s</em>.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py method">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"frozenset.isdisjoint">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">frozenset.</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">isdisjoint=
