<section id=3D"special-attributes-of-genericalias-objects">
<h4>Special Attributes of <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><spa=
n class=3D"pre">GenericAlias</span></code> objects<a class=3D"headerlink" h=
ref=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#special-attributes-o=
f-genericalias-objects" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h4>
<p>All parameterized generics implement special read-only attributes.</p>
<dl class=3D"py attribute">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"genericalias.__origin__">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">genericalias.=
</span></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">__origi=
n__</span></span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/stdtypes.html#genericalias.__origin__" title=3D"Link to this defini=
tion">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>This attribute points at the non-parameterized generic class:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">list</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><=
span class=3D"nb">int</span><span class=3D"p">]</span><span class=3D"o">.</=
span><span class=3D"n">__origin__</span>
<span class=3D"go">&lt;class 'list'&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py attribute">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"genericalias.__args__">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">genericalias.=
</span></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">__args_=
_</span></span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/stdtypes.html#genericalias.__args__" title=3D"Link to this definition=
">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>This attribute is a <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://=
docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#tuple" title=3D"tuple"><code class=
=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tupl=
e</span></code></a> (possibly of length 1) of generic
types passed to the original <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https:=
//docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__class_getitem__" titl=
e=3D"object.__class_getitem__"><code class=3D"xref py py-meth docutils lite=
ral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">__class_getitem__()</span></code></a> =
of the
generic class:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">dict</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><=
span class=3D"nb">str</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"nb">l=
ist</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"nb">int</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">]]</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">__args__</span=
>
<span class=3D"go">(&lt;class 'str'&gt;, list[int])</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py attribute">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"genericalias.__parameters__">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">genericalias.=
</span></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">__param=
eters__</span></span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.or=
g/3/library/stdtypes.html#genericalias.__parameters__" title=3D"Link to thi=
s definition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>This attribute is a lazily computed tuple (possibly empty) of unique=
 type
variables found in <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">__args__</span></code>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"kn">from</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><=
span class=3D"nn">typing</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"kn"=
>import</span> <span class=3D"n">TypeVar</span>

<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">T</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">TypeVar</span><span class=3D"p">(</sp=
an><span class=3D"s1">'T'</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"nb">list</span><span =
class=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D"n">T</span><span class=3D"p">]</span><sp=
an class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">__parameters__</span>
<span class=3D"go">(~T,)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>A <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Gener=
icAlias</span></code> object with <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"h=
ttps://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.ParamSpec" title=3D"typ=
ing.ParamSpec"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">typing.ParamSpec</span></code></a> parameters may not
have correct <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">__parameters__</span></code> after substitution because
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/t=
yping.html#typing.ParamSpec" title=3D"typing.ParamSpec"><code class=3D"xref=
 py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">typing.Param=
Spec</span></code></a> is intended primarily for static type checking.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"py attribute">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object py" id=3D"genericalias.__unpacked__">
<span class=3D"sig-prename descclassname"><span class=3D"pre">genericalias.=
</span></span><span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">__unpac=
ked__</span></span><a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/=
3/library/stdtypes.html#genericalias.__unpacked__" title=3D"Link to this de=
finition">=C2=B6</a></dt>
<dd><p>A boolean that is true if the alias has been unpacked using the
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">*</span></=
code> operator (see <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.py=
thon.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.TypeVarTuple" title=3D"typing.TypeVar=
Tuple"><code class=3D"xref py py-data docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">TypeVarTuple</span></code></a>).</p>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.11.</span></p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

