<section id=3D"union-type">
<span id=3D"types-union"></span><h3>Union Type<a class=3D"headerlink" href=
=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#union-type" title=3D"Li=
nk to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p id=3D"index-60">A union object holds the value of the <code class=3D"doc=
utils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">|</span></code> (bitwise or)=
 operation on
multiple <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/stdtypes.html#bltin-type-objects"><span class=3D"std std-ref">type =
objects</span></a>.  These types are intended
primarily for <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.o=
rg/3/glossary.html#term-annotation"><span class=3D"xref std std-term">type =
annotations</span></a>. The union type expression
enables cleaner type hinting syntax compared to subscripting <a class=3D"re=
ference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typ=
ing.Union" title=3D"typing.Union"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils =
literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">typing.Union</span></code></a>.</p=
>
<dl class=3D"describe">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object">
<span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">X</span> <span class=
=3D"pre">|</span> <span class=3D"pre">Y</span> <span class=3D"pre">|</span>=
 <span class=3D"pre">...</span></span></dt>
<dd><p>Defines a union object which holds types <em>X</em>, <em>Y</em>, and=
 so forth. <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre"=
>X</span> <span class=3D"pre">|</span> <span class=3D"pre">Y</span></code>
means either X or Y.  It is equivalent to <code class=3D"docutils literal n=
otranslate"><span class=3D"pre">typing.Union[X,</span> <span class=3D"pre">=
Y]</span></code>.
For example, the following function expects an argument of type
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/f=
unctions.html#int" title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int</span></code></a> or <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions=
.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span></code></a>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"k">def=
</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">square</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">number</span><span class=3D"p">:</span> <=
span class=3D"nb">int</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">=
float</span><span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">-&gt;</span> <span=
 class=3D"nb">int</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">floa=
t</span><span class=3D"p">:</span>
    <span class=3D"k">return</span> <span class=3D"n">number</span> <span c=
lass=3D"o">**</span> <span class=3D"mi">2</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>The <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">|</=
span></code> operand cannot be used at runtime to define unions where one o=
r
more members is a forward reference. For example, <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int</span> <span class=3D"pre">|</s=
pan> <span class=3D"pre">"Foo"</span></code>, where
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">"Foo"</spa=
n></code> is a reference to a class not yet defined, will fail at
runtime. For unions which include forward references, present the
whole expression as a string, e.g. <code class=3D"docutils literal notransl=
ate"><span class=3D"pre">"int</span> <span class=3D"pre">|</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"pre">Foo"</span></code>.</p>
</div>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"describe">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object">
<span class=3D"sig-name descname"><span class=3D"pre">union_object</span> <=
span class=3D"pre">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"pre">other</span></span></d=
t>
<dd><p>Union objects can be tested for equality with other union objects.  =
Details:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Unions of unions are flattened:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"p">(</=
span><span class=3D"nb">int</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=
=3D"nb">str</span><span class=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <sp=
an class=3D"nb">float</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D=
"nb">int</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span> <s=
pan class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">float</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
<li><p>Redundant types are removed:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"nb">in=
t</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">int</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D=3D</s=
pan> <span class=3D"nb">int</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=
=3D"nb">str</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
<li><p>When comparing unions, the order is ignored:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"nb">in=
t</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span> <span class=3D"o">|</s=
pan> <span class=3D"nb">int</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
<li><p>It creates instances of <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.Union" title=3D"typing.Uni=
on"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">typing.Union</span></code></a>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"nb">in=
t</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">typing</span><span class=3D"o">.</=
span><span class=3D"n">Union</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><span class=3D=
"nb">int</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">]</span>
<span class=3D"nb">type</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"nb">=
int</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"nb">str</span><span cl=
ass=3D"p">)</span> <span class=3D"ow">is</span> <span class=3D"n">typing</s=
pan><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">Union</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
<li><p>Optional types can be spelled as a union with <code class=3D"docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">None</span></code>:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"nb">st=
r</span> <span class=3D"o">|</span> <span class=3D"kc">None</span> <span cl=
ass=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">typing</span><span class=3D"o">.<=
/span><span class=3D"n">Optional</span><span class=3D"p">[</span><span clas=
s=3D"nb">str</span><span class=3D"p">]</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
</ul>
</dd></dl>

<dl class=3D"describe">
<dt class=3D"sig sig-object">
