</div>
<section id=3D"affected-apis">
<h3>Affected APIs<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/=
library/stdtypes.html#affected-apis" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6<=
/a></h3>
<p>The limitation only applies to potentially slow conversions between <a c=
lass=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/funct=
ions.html#int" title=3D"int"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int</span></code></a>
and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/libra=
ry/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutil=
s literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str</span></code></a> or <a clas=
s=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes=
.html#bytes" title=3D"bytes"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">bytes</span></code></a>:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int=
(string)</span></code> with default base 10.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int=
(string,</span> <span class=3D"pre">base)</span></code> for all bases that =
are not a power of 2.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str=
(integer)</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">rep=
r(integer)</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p>any other string conversion to base 10, for example <code class=3D"d=
ocutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">f"{integer}"</span></code>=
,
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">"{}".forma=
t(integer)</span></code>, or <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><=
span class=3D"pre">b"%d"</span> <span class=3D"pre">%</span> <span class=3D=
"pre">integer</span></code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The limitations do not apply to functions with a linear algorithm:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int=
(string,</span> <span class=3D"pre">base)</span></code> with base 2, 4, 8, =
16, or 32.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/stdtypes.html#int.from_bytes" title=3D"int.from_bytes"><code class=3D=
"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">int.from=
_bytes()</span></code></a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"http=
s://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#int.to_bytes" title=3D"int.to_b=
ytes"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">int.to_bytes()</span></code></a>.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/functions.html#hex" title=3D"hex"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docu=
tils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">hex()</span></code></a>, <a c=
lass=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/funct=
ions.html#oct" title=3D"oct"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">oct()</span></code></a>, <a class=3D"ref=
erence internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#b=
in" title=3D"bin"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notransla=
te"><span class=3D"pre">bin()</span></code></a>.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/string.html#formatspec"><span class=3D"std std-ref">Format Specificat=
ion Mini-Language</span></a> for hex, octal, and binary numbers.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docu=
tils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str</span></code></a> to <a c=
lass=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/funct=
ions.html#float" title=3D"float"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">float</span></code></a>.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/stdtypes.html#str" title=3D"str"><code class=3D"xref py py-class docu=
tils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str</span></code></a> to <a c=
lass=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/decim=
al.html#decimal.Decimal" title=3D"decimal.Decimal"><code class=3D"xref py p=
y-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">decimal.Decimal</=
span></code></a>.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id=3D"configuring-the-limit">
<h3>Configuring the limit<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.pytho=
n.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#configuring-the-limit" title=3D"Link to this =
heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p>Before Python starts up you can use an environment variable or an interp=
reter
command line flag to configure the limit:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><span class=3D"target" id=3D"index-69"></span><a class=3D"reference =
internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#envvar-PYTHO=
NINTMAXSTRDIGITS"><code class=3D"xref std std-envvar docutils literal notra=
nslate"><span class=3D"pre">PYTHONINTMAXSTRDIGITS</span></code></a>, e.g.
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">PYTHONINTM=
AXSTRDIGITS=3D640</span> <span class=3D"pre">python3</span></code> to set t=
he limit to 640 or
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">PYTHONINTM=
AXSTRDIGITS=3D0</span> <span class=3D"pre">python3</span></code> to disable=
 the limitation.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/us=
ing/cmdline.html#cmdoption-X"><code class=3D"xref std std-option docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-X</span> <span class=3D"pre">int_m=
ax_str_digits</span></code></a>, e.g.
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">python3</s=
pan> <span class=3D"pre">-X</span> <span class=3D"pre">int_max_str_digits=
=3D640</span></code></p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/sys.html#sys.flags.int_max_str_digits" title=3D"sys.flags.int_max_str=
_digits"><code class=3D"xref py py-data docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">sys.flags.int_max_str_digits</span></code></a> contains the =
value of
<span class=3D"target" id=3D"index-70"></span><a class=3D"reference interna=
l" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#envvar-PYTHONINTMAX=
STRDIGITS"><code class=3D"xref std std-envvar docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">PYTHONINTMAXSTRDIGITS</span></code></a> or <a class=3D=
"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#c=
mdoption-X"><code class=3D"xref std std-option docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">-X</span> <span class=3D"pre">int_max_str_digits</spa=
n></code></a>.
If both the env var and the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><s=
pan class=3D"pre">-X</span></code> option are set, the <code class=3D"docut=
ils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">-X</span></code> option takes
precedence. A value of <em>-1</em> indicates that both were unset, thus a v=
alue of
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
ys.html#sys.int_info.default_max_str_digits" title=3D"sys.int_info.default_=
max_str_digits"><code class=3D"xref py py-data docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">sys.int_info.default_max_str_digits</span></code></a>=
 was used during initialization.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>From code, you can inspect the current limit and set a new one using the=
se
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/s=
ys.html#module-sys" title=3D"sys: Access system-specific parameters and fun=
ctions."><code class=3D"xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">sys</span></code></a> APIs:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/sys.html#sys.get_int_max_str_digits" title=3D"sys.get_int_max_str_dig=
its"><code class=3D"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span cla=
ss=3D"pre">sys.get_int_max_str_digits()</span></code></a> and <a class=3D"r=
eference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.html#sys.s=
et_int_max_str_digits" title=3D"sys.set_int_max_str_digits"><code class=3D"=
xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.set_i=
nt_max_str_digits()</span></code></a> are
a getter and setter for the interpreter-wide limit. Subinterpreters have
their own limit.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Information about the default and minimum can be found in <a class=3D"re=
ference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.html#sys.in=
t_info" title=3D"sys.int_info"><code class=3D"xref py py-data docutils lite=
ral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.int_info</span></code></a>:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/sys.html#sys.int_info" title=3D"sys.int_info"><code class=3D"xref py =
py-data docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.int_info.defa=
ult_max_str_digits</span></code></a> is the compiled-in
default limit.</p></li>
<li><p><a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.org/3/li=
brary/sys.html#sys.int_info" title=3D"sys.int_info"><code class=3D"xref py =
py-data docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.int_info.str_=
digits_check_threshold</span></code></a> is the lowest
accepted value for the limit (other than 0 which disables it).</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"versionadded">
<p><span class=3D"versionmodified added">Added in version 3.11.</span></p>
</div>
<div class=3D"admonition caution">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Caution</p>
<p>Setting a low limit <em>can</em> lead to problems. While rare, code exis=
ts that
contains integer constants in decimal in their source that exceed the
minimum threshold. A consequence of setting the limit is that Python source
code containing decimal integer literals longer than the limit will
encounter an error during parsing, usually at startup time or import time o=
r
even at installation time - anytime an up to date <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">.pyc</span></code> does not already
exist for the code. A workaround for source that contains such large
constants is to convert them to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">0x</span></code> hexadecimal form as it has no limit.=
</p>
<p>Test your application thoroughly if you use a low limit. Ensure your tes=
ts
run with the limit set early via the environment or flag so that it applies
during startup and even during any installation step that may invoke Python
to precompile <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"p=
re">.py</span></code> sources to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">.pyc</span></code> files.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"recommended-configuration">
<h3>Recommended configuration<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.p=
ython.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#recommended-configuration" title=3D"Link =
to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h3>
<p>The default <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.python.=
org/3/library/sys.html#sys.int_info.default_max_str_digits" title=3D"sys.in=
t_info.default_max_str_digits"><code class=3D"xref py py-data docutils lite=
ral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">sys.int_info.default_max_str_digits</s=
pan></code></a> is expected to be
reasonable for most applications. If your application requires a different
limit, set it from your main entry point using Python version agnostic code=
 as
these APIs were added in security patch releases in versions before 3.12.</=
p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-python3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight" style=
=3D"position: relative;"><button class=3D"copybutton" type=3D"button" title=
=3D"Copy to clipboard">Copy</button><pre><span></span><span class=3D"gp">&g=
t;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"kn">import</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"nn">sys</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"k">if</span> <span cl=
